WEBVTT

00:07.583 --> 00:08.666
[man clears throat]

00:09.750 --> 00:11.041
[gavel banging]

00:11.125 --> 00:12.666
Let's get to it.

00:12.750 --> 00:14.041
All those in favor…

00:16.291 --> 00:17.625
All opposed.

00:20.666 --> 00:24.291
Well, the PTA has an accepted
set of rules concerning the prom.

00:24.375 --> 00:26.750
Young ladies must wear
non-revealing dresses.

00:26.833 --> 00:29.083
Young men must wear suits or tuxes.

00:29.166 --> 00:32.666
And if a student chooses to bring a date,
they must be of the opposite sex.

00:32.750 --> 00:34.916
Well, can't you just ban this student?

00:35.000 --> 00:38.125
Well, we've been advised
that there may be some legal repercussions

00:38.208 --> 00:40.166
if we prevent this girl from attending,

00:40.250 --> 00:42.833
so although it breaks my heart,
we have no choice.

00:42.916 --> 00:45.458
-There won't be a prom.
-[reporter 1] Mrs. Greene, a question.

00:45.541 --> 00:48.125
[reporter 2] Have you asked the students
what they think of this?

00:48.208 --> 00:50.000
[reporter 1]
Are you choosing not to comment?

00:50.083 --> 00:52.291
[reporter 2] Hey, there's Emma!
Can we get a comment?

00:52.375 --> 00:54.083
[reporter 3] Can you answer
some questions?

00:54.166 --> 00:55.625
[reporter 1] Can we get a statement?

00:55.708 --> 00:59.291
[reporter 2] Emma, what do you think
of the PTA's decision to cancel prom?

00:59.375 --> 01:01.083
[reporter 1] Emma, do you have a response?

01:03.708 --> 01:05.708
[upbeat music playing]

01:42.083 --> 01:44.041
-[indistinct chatter]
-[horns honking]

01:44.125 --> 01:46.791
[Frank] It's Frank DiLella
with New York 1's On Stage.

01:46.875 --> 01:50.916
We're here for the opening night
of Eleanor! The Eleanor Roosevelt Musical,

01:51.000 --> 01:54.166
starring the incomparable Dee Dee Allen.

01:54.250 --> 01:58.625
-Dee Dee! You're a Broadway star.
-Yes, I am. [chuckles]

01:58.708 --> 02:02.166
You have your choice of roles.
What drew you to Eleanor?

02:02.250 --> 02:07.250
Well, Eleanor Roosevelt
was a brave, powerful, charismatic woman

02:07.333 --> 02:09.250
who no one had ever heard of.

02:09.333 --> 02:10.958
Her story needs to be told.

02:11.041 --> 02:15.416
People need to know
it is possible to change the world,

02:15.500 --> 02:18.791
whether you're
a homely middle-aged First Lady

02:18.875 --> 02:21.250
or a Broadway star! [chuckles]

02:21.333 --> 02:24.458
Barry Glickman! You were brilliant as FDR.

02:24.541 --> 02:26.666
From the moment
I first stepped into FDR's shoes…

02:26.750 --> 02:28.916
And when I say "shoes," I mean wheelchair.

02:29.000 --> 02:30.083
…I had an epiphany.

02:30.166 --> 02:32.708
I realized there is no difference

02:32.791 --> 02:36.375
between the president of the United States
and a celebrity.

02:36.458 --> 02:40.583
We both have power.
The power to change the world.

02:40.666 --> 02:43.250
It's a weighty responsibility.

02:43.333 --> 02:44.791
Let's talk process.

02:44.875 --> 02:47.833
♪ When I'm in character, I go insane ♪

02:48.416 --> 02:50.750
♪ I stagger, I stammer, I sob ♪

02:51.791 --> 02:54.500
♪ I make the audiences feel my pain ♪

02:54.583 --> 02:58.416
♪ And if they don't leave depressed
Then I've not done my job ♪

02:58.500 --> 03:01.666
♪ Each time I find a role like Eleanor ♪

03:01.750 --> 03:04.958
♪ The artist inside of me thrives ♪

03:05.041 --> 03:08.416
♪ I put on that wig
And those prosthetic teeth ♪

03:08.500 --> 03:11.916
♪ And know I'm changing lives ♪

03:12.500 --> 03:18.333
♪ By the time I get tuberculosis
In act two ♪

03:18.916 --> 03:21.875
♪ Even the people who are dead inside ♪

03:21.958 --> 03:24.666
♪ Will shout, "Bravo," on cue! ♪

03:24.750 --> 03:26.083
[all] Bravo!

03:27.541 --> 03:30.041
The first review is in.
New Jersey Star-Ledger.

03:30.125 --> 03:31.541
Don't tell me…

03:32.291 --> 03:35.458
unless it's a rave or a mixed-positive.

03:36.041 --> 03:37.291
It says we're a hit!

03:37.375 --> 03:38.958
-[gasps]
-[all cheering]

03:39.041 --> 03:41.791
[screams] Oh, my God!

03:41.875 --> 03:43.125
[car horn honks]

03:49.375 --> 03:50.750
[Barry chuckles]

03:53.708 --> 03:57.000
♪ We're a hit and I think we deserve it ♪

03:57.083 --> 03:59.791
♪ That's for sure ♪

03:59.875 --> 04:03.083
♪ Also, it means that this tour de force ♪

04:03.166 --> 04:05.375
♪ Will not be forced to tour ♪

04:05.458 --> 04:08.375
[Dee Dee] To Eleanor!
May she run for eternity!

04:08.458 --> 04:10.125
[all] To Eleanor!

04:11.916 --> 04:14.541
♪ Cheers to a show that's so inspiring ♪

04:15.208 --> 04:18.250
♪ It's almost too much to sit through ♪

04:18.833 --> 04:21.500
♪ And if we run
That might mean one more thing ♪

04:21.583 --> 04:23.208
♪ That in ten years or so ♪

04:23.291 --> 04:25.333
♪ We'll do Eleanor Two! ♪

04:25.416 --> 04:28.625
♪ I can predict
What the reviews will say ♪

04:28.708 --> 04:31.833
♪ Before the next notice arrives ♪

04:31.916 --> 04:33.000
♪ It's ground-breaking ♪

04:33.083 --> 04:34.666
-♪ Earth-shaking! ♪
-♪ Life-affirming! ♪

04:34.750 --> 04:36.375
-♪ Breathtaking ♪
-♪ Gut-wrenching! ♪

04:36.458 --> 04:38.833
-♪ Heart-aching ♪
-♪ In two words, it's history-making ♪

04:38.916 --> 04:40.875
♪ That's why every actor strives ♪

04:40.958 --> 04:44.333
♪ For adulation ♪

04:44.416 --> 04:47.708
♪ And compensation ♪

04:47.791 --> 04:50.375
♪ That comes from nightly ♪

04:50.458 --> 04:57.333
♪ Changing lives! ♪

04:57.416 --> 04:59.041
It's just what we do.

04:59.125 --> 05:00.958
The rest of the reviews are coming in!

05:01.041 --> 05:02.166
[all exclaim]

05:02.250 --> 05:05.666
New York Post,
Associated Press, New York Times.

05:05.750 --> 05:07.750
-[all gasp]
-The New York Times!

05:08.583 --> 05:09.416
Wow…

05:13.541 --> 05:14.541
[Dee Dee] What?

05:15.333 --> 05:16.750
-[Sheldon] Wow…
-What's happening?

05:16.833 --> 05:20.166
This is not a review you want
when you have crappy advance sales.

05:20.250 --> 05:21.875
This is gonna close us.

05:22.625 --> 05:25.041
What didn't they like? Was it the hip-hop?

05:25.125 --> 05:27.083
Yes, but not only that.

05:27.166 --> 05:30.833
-For God's sake, Sheldon. Just read it.
-What? Read.

05:30.916 --> 05:33.250
[Sheldon] Okay, just the highlights.

05:33.333 --> 05:37.208
"Barry Glickman's FDR might just be
the most insultingly misguided,

05:37.291 --> 05:39.500
offensive, and laughable performance

05:39.583 --> 05:44.000
that this reviewer has ever had
the squirming misfortune to endure."

05:46.750 --> 05:48.208
That's not so bad.

05:48.833 --> 05:51.166
-Do her. Do her.
-I'm just saying.

05:51.250 --> 05:52.083
Oh? Mmm.

05:52.166 --> 05:54.416
"Watching Dee Dee Allen's
Eleanor Roosevelt

05:54.500 --> 05:57.208
croaking out a heavy-handed
message of activism

05:57.291 --> 05:59.708
is like paying an aging drag queen

05:59.791 --> 06:03.041
to shove a syrup-soaked
American flag down my throat."

06:03.625 --> 06:05.208
Well, that…

06:05.291 --> 06:07.916
That's not criticism.

06:08.000 --> 06:12.250
That's just… It's just a per…
[voice breaking] …a personal attack.

06:12.333 --> 06:16.833
"If you're considering buying a ticket
to this show, do yourself a favor."

06:16.916 --> 06:19.791
"Buy a few feet
of good, heavy rope instead

06:19.875 --> 06:21.666
and then go hang yourself."

06:21.750 --> 06:25.541
[Barry] Oh, God! Oh, God!

06:26.666 --> 06:29.416
[mutters] What?
Was the show really that bad?

06:29.500 --> 06:32.333
It's not the show. It's you two.

06:32.416 --> 06:34.208
You're just not likeable.

06:34.916 --> 06:35.916
-What?
-What?

06:36.000 --> 06:38.291
Nobody likes a narcissist.

06:39.208 --> 06:40.708
-Oh, this… [clears throat]
-Oh, that.

06:40.791 --> 06:44.291
Leave it to me. I'll go and try
and change the narrative once again.

06:44.375 --> 06:48.791
-I hate this world! This is bullshit!
-Just horrible. It's just… It hurts.

06:48.875 --> 06:52.000
It… It hurts my heart.

06:52.083 --> 06:54.375
-[Barry exhales]
-Where did everybody go?

06:55.333 --> 06:58.583
-What can I get you?
-[both] Yola Mezcal blackberry smash.

06:59.166 --> 07:01.250
[bartender] My condolences, Dee Dee.

07:01.333 --> 07:03.791
But remember, you have friends.

07:03.875 --> 07:06.458
Thank you. Who are you?

07:07.500 --> 07:08.583
Trent Oliver.

07:09.291 --> 07:10.541
Uh, oh…

07:11.041 --> 07:14.125
-We've done five shows together.
-Oh, really? Oh, my God.

07:14.208 --> 07:16.375
Trent went to Juilliard.
Won't shut up about it.

07:16.458 --> 07:19.583
-Oh, right, Trent! Of course, Trent!
-Trent.

07:19.666 --> 07:20.791
[Trent and Dee Dee chuckle]

07:22.166 --> 07:23.541
Why are you dressed like a waiter?

07:24.583 --> 07:26.916
-I'm in between gigs at the moment.
-[Dee Dee] Hmm.

07:27.000 --> 07:31.500
Honestly, Dee Dee, I feel adrift
as I did in my days before Juilliard.

07:31.583 --> 07:32.666
Oh, my God.

07:32.750 --> 07:35.875
You see, my passions are fueled
by the power of Lady Theater

07:35.958 --> 07:39.000
and how she can,
with a gentle touch of her hand,

07:39.083 --> 07:41.083
sculpt a human soul.

07:41.166 --> 07:43.833
-But we learned at Juilliard…
-Oh, mother of God.

07:43.916 --> 07:47.791
If I could soliloquize,
"If you prick me, do I not bleed?"

07:49.666 --> 07:52.541
"And if you do not pay me,
do I not still act?"

07:52.625 --> 07:54.208
That might be enough.

07:54.291 --> 07:56.000
Still, I have played Hamlet,

07:56.083 --> 08:01.875
and yet I'm only known as that guy
from the beloved early aughts' sitcom…

08:02.458 --> 08:03.708
[Trent] Talk to the Hand.

08:03.791 --> 08:05.041
["Hold My Hand" playing]

08:05.125 --> 08:06.541
[audience laughing]

08:07.875 --> 08:10.791
I question
the very meaning of my existence.

08:10.875 --> 08:12.916
[jazzy tune playing]

08:13.000 --> 08:17.125
Maggie Smith once approached me
in a men's bathroom and she said,

08:17.208 --> 08:19.791
"Who sent you? Was it Michelle Dockery?"

08:19.875 --> 08:23.708
"Because the court said 500 yards."
You could tell she was scared.

08:23.791 --> 08:26.958
-Hey, guys!
-[Barry] Angie! Angie.

08:27.041 --> 08:30.291
I'm sorry your show
closed on opening night again!

08:30.375 --> 08:31.916
[Barry and Dee Dee groan]

08:32.416 --> 08:35.083
Welcome to the world
of the unemployed. Top me off.

08:35.166 --> 08:36.750
I thought you were in Chicago.

08:36.833 --> 08:39.583
[groans] I just quit.

08:40.208 --> 08:43.708
Twenty years in the chorus and they still
wouldn't let me play Roxie Hart.

08:43.791 --> 08:45.958
-[Dee Dee] Aw.
-You wanna know who's playing the role?

08:46.041 --> 08:47.416
-Kelly Ripa?
-Cher?

08:47.500 --> 08:49.166
-Connie Chung.
-Kris Jenner?

08:49.250 --> 08:50.833
No, Tina Louise.

08:51.750 --> 08:53.916
Ginger from Gilligan's Island.

08:54.000 --> 08:55.625
Oh, my God, is she still alive?

08:56.708 --> 08:58.666
[laughs]

09:04.416 --> 09:05.625
[sighs]

09:09.916 --> 09:12.250
We're wasting our lives.

09:12.333 --> 09:16.250
Hmm, it's true.
At least we're all in the same boat.

09:16.333 --> 09:20.416
"Misery acquaints a man
with strange bedfellows."

09:20.500 --> 09:22.583
-[Barry] Oh, my God.
-That's from The Tempest.

09:22.666 --> 09:26.541
Okay, one, shut up.
Two, I refuse to give up, okay?

09:26.625 --> 09:30.458
We're… We're still celebrities.
We still have power.

09:30.541 --> 09:31.666
[chuckles]

09:31.750 --> 09:34.166
Now, The Times
sort of castrated you as it were.

09:34.250 --> 09:35.083
[Barry sighs]

09:35.166 --> 09:38.416
Yep. They wrote you off
as aging narcissists.

09:38.500 --> 09:41.375
I still don't understand
what's wrong with that.

09:41.458 --> 09:45.625
There's a very simple way
that we can still love ourselves

09:45.708 --> 09:50.500
yet appear to be
decent human beings, okay?

09:50.583 --> 09:53.166
We will become celebrity activists.

09:53.250 --> 09:55.500
-[Angie] Oh! Brilliant!
-[Barry] Right?

09:55.583 --> 09:57.875
-All we need is a cause.
-A cause célèbre.

09:57.958 --> 10:00.375
Everybody think of some causes. Go.

10:00.458 --> 10:02.416
-Um, poverty?
-Too big.

10:02.500 --> 10:03.750
World hunger.

10:03.833 --> 10:07.625
That is also a major thing.
No, we need something we can handle.

10:07.708 --> 10:11.166
Some little injustice
we can drive to. Recycling.

10:11.250 --> 10:13.541
-Let's see what's trending.
-[Barry] Recycling's good.

10:13.625 --> 10:16.833
-Why are there so many award shows?
-Parking.

10:16.916 --> 10:20.000
-[Barry] Or the TVs in the back of cabs.
-Oh! Oh, yeah, what about this girl?

10:20.875 --> 10:22.750
Oh, my gosh. Check this out.

10:22.833 --> 10:24.541
-[Barry] What girl?
-It's all over Twitter.

10:24.625 --> 10:25.458
[Barry] Oh.

10:26.125 --> 10:28.166
She's from Edgewater, Indiana.

10:29.166 --> 10:33.291
She's a lesbian. She wanted to take
her girlfriend to the high school prom,

10:33.375 --> 10:35.958
and the PTA went apeshit
and they canceled it.

10:36.041 --> 10:38.000
They canceled prom?

10:38.083 --> 10:40.125
-Are they allowed to do that?
-No.

10:40.208 --> 10:42.125
[reporter] Principal Hawkins,
your response.

10:42.208 --> 10:45.000
The first thing I'm going to do
is contact the Indiana state's attorney.

10:45.083 --> 10:48.416
This is not about school rules.
This is a civil rights case.

10:48.500 --> 10:49.583
Wait, seriously?

10:49.666 --> 10:53.458
I'm betting pressure from the state's
attorney will stop these bigots cold.

10:53.541 --> 10:55.541
It better.
Because I'll tell you this much.

10:55.625 --> 10:58.000
If word gets out,
people are gonna get mad.

10:58.083 --> 10:59.375
This pisses me off.

11:00.000 --> 11:02.500
The next thing you know,
some modern-day Eleanor Roosevelt

11:02.583 --> 11:05.375
is gonna march down here
and all hell's gonna break loose.

11:06.833 --> 11:09.791
We have got to go down there
and raise holy hell.

11:09.875 --> 11:12.333
We will be the biggest thing
to happen in Indiana

11:12.416 --> 11:14.625
since… whatever's happened in Indiana.

11:14.708 --> 11:17.708
-So this is it? This is our cause?
-Yes. Are you with me?

11:17.791 --> 11:19.541
[all cheer]

11:19.625 --> 11:21.166
-We'll have a rally!
-Yes!

11:21.250 --> 11:24.375
-We'll have picket signs!
-We'll make T-shirts.

11:24.458 --> 11:26.666
We'll get Sheldon to tag along.
He can find us a venue.

11:26.750 --> 11:28.208
Oh, wow!

11:28.291 --> 11:32.125
-Can we actually do this?
-You bet your sweet MILF ass we can!

11:32.208 --> 11:33.500
[all laughing]

11:33.583 --> 11:34.666
[exhales]

11:36.541 --> 11:38.000
We are gonna prove…

11:38.666 --> 11:40.875
♪ That in this day and age ♪

11:40.958 --> 11:45.166
♪ Being gay isn't a crime ♪

11:45.875 --> 11:52.583
♪ This is our moment to change the world ♪

11:53.333 --> 11:56.125
-♪ One lesbian… ♪
-[Trent] ♪ Lesbian ♪

11:56.208 --> 11:59.000
-[Dee Dee] ♪ Lesbian ♪
-[Angie] ♪ Lesbian ♪

11:59.916 --> 12:03.000
♪ At a time! ♪

12:05.583 --> 12:08.708
♪ We're gonna help that little lesbian ♪

12:08.791 --> 12:10.916
♪ Whether she likes it or not ♪

12:12.208 --> 12:14.708
♪ When you're a legendary thespian ♪

12:14.791 --> 12:16.416
♪ First, you help the distressed ♪

12:16.500 --> 12:18.125
♪ Then you help the distraught ♪

12:18.833 --> 12:21.958
♪ We're going down
To where the necks are red ♪

12:22.041 --> 12:25.125
♪ And lack of dentistry thrives ♪

12:25.208 --> 12:28.250
♪ Why sing and dance
When you can take a stance! ♪

12:28.333 --> 12:31.791
♪ And know you're truly changing lives ♪

12:32.541 --> 12:35.750
Okay, now we have got to get an anthem!

12:35.833 --> 12:38.375
-Like "We Are The World."
-Yes, but for lesbians.

12:38.458 --> 12:41.333
Steve Sondheim'll write us something.
He's a big fan of my Sweeney Todd.

12:41.416 --> 12:42.250
I'll handle this.

12:42.333 --> 12:44.291
Wait. How are we gonna get there?

12:44.375 --> 12:48.916
I just booked a non-union tour of Godspell
and it goes straight through Indiana.

12:49.000 --> 12:53.333
-You can come with us on the bus.
-See? It's all coming together!

12:54.666 --> 12:58.083
♪ We're gonna march
Until that town looks like ♪

12:58.166 --> 13:02.083
♪ The end of act one of Les Mis ♪

13:02.166 --> 13:05.458
♪ You don't gotta have a PhD in psych ♪

13:05.541 --> 13:09.333
♪ To know that people kowtow
To the folks in the biz ♪

13:09.416 --> 13:12.541
♪ We're gonna teach them to be more PC ♪

13:12.625 --> 13:15.541
-♪ The minute our group arrives ♪
-That's right!

13:15.625 --> 13:17.750
-♪ Those fist-pumping ♪
-♪ Bible-thumping ♪

13:17.833 --> 13:19.458
-♪ Spam-eating ♪
-♪ Cousin-loving ♪

13:19.541 --> 13:21.208
-♪ Cow-tipping ♪
-♪ Shoulder-slumping ♪

13:21.291 --> 13:22.875
-♪ Finger-wagging ♪
-♪ Hoosier-humping ♪

13:22.958 --> 13:24.875
♪ Losers and their homely wives ♪

13:24.958 --> 13:28.291
♪ They'll learn compassion! ♪

13:28.375 --> 13:31.666
♪ And better fashion ♪

13:31.750 --> 13:34.625
♪ Once we at last start ♪

13:34.708 --> 13:40.750
♪ Changing lives! ♪

13:40.833 --> 13:42.666
Now let's go start a fight.

13:42.750 --> 13:43.958
[bell rings]

13:44.041 --> 13:45.375
[indistinct chatter]

13:56.916 --> 13:58.458
[girl] Do you like the bears?

13:59.083 --> 14:01.666
Yeah, you know,
I'm pretty sure this breaks a few laws.

14:01.750 --> 14:06.041
-It's our way of saying thank you, Emma.
-Yeah. Thanks for canceling prom.

14:06.125 --> 14:08.625
I didn't cancel prom. Your parents did.

14:08.708 --> 14:10.166
Come on. Lay off her.

14:10.250 --> 14:12.500
-Oh, are you on her side now?
-[scoffs] No.

14:12.583 --> 14:15.708
I'm just not in third grade.
See you at practice.

14:16.458 --> 14:19.291
Unlike your social life, this isn't over.

14:26.000 --> 14:27.458
♪ Note to self ♪

14:27.541 --> 14:29.666
♪ Don't be gay in Indiana ♪

14:31.625 --> 14:35.458
♪ Big heads-up
That's a really stupid plan ♪

14:36.666 --> 14:39.458
♪ There are places
Where it's in to be out ♪

14:39.541 --> 14:42.291
♪ Maybe San Francisco or thereabout ♪

14:42.375 --> 14:45.291
♪ But in Indiana, without a doubt ♪

14:45.375 --> 14:50.333
♪ If you're not straight
Then guess what's bound to hit the fan? ♪

14:51.833 --> 14:54.916
♪ Just breathe, Emma ♪

14:55.000 --> 14:57.250
♪ Not everyone is that repressed ♪

14:57.333 --> 15:00.041
♪ Just breathe, Emma ♪

15:00.125 --> 15:02.958
♪ It wouldn't be high school
Without a test ♪

15:03.041 --> 15:05.833
♪ Just close your eyes and count to ten ♪

15:05.916 --> 15:08.083
♪ Go to your happy place ♪

15:08.166 --> 15:11.375
♪ And then try not to combust ♪

15:12.625 --> 15:15.750
♪ Just breathe ♪

15:16.500 --> 15:17.666
[whistle blows]

15:17.750 --> 15:19.166
[indistinct chatter]

15:23.458 --> 15:27.833
Hey, Emma. Hey, who's this girl
you were gonna bring to the prom, anyway?

15:27.916 --> 15:30.125
I didn't know we had
more than one lesbo in town.

15:30.208 --> 15:33.458
-You don't know her. She's new here.
-Like an exchange student?

15:33.541 --> 15:34.625
[whistle blows]

15:34.708 --> 15:35.958
-Maybe.
-Mmm.

15:36.041 --> 15:38.833
Well, then why don't you, like,
exchange her for a guy?

15:38.916 --> 15:40.541
Ooh! Dude! Nice!

15:45.625 --> 15:49.291
♪ Note to self
People suck in Indiana ♪

15:49.791 --> 15:50.625
[sighs]

15:51.166 --> 15:56.083
♪ Leave today
Pray the Greyhound isn't full ♪

15:56.166 --> 15:59.125
♪ Who knew asking out a girl to the prom ♪

15:59.208 --> 16:01.541
♪ Would go over just like an atom bomb ♪

16:01.625 --> 16:06.750
♪ And make things much worse
With your dad and mom ♪

16:06.833 --> 16:11.916
♪ And who'd have ever thought
That could be possible? ♪

16:13.291 --> 16:16.500
♪ Just breathe, Emma ♪

16:16.583 --> 16:18.916
♪ Picture a beach with golden sand ♪

16:19.000 --> 16:22.041
♪ Just breathe, Emma ♪

16:22.125 --> 16:24.041
♪ Picture a Xanax in your hand ♪

16:24.125 --> 16:27.583
♪ Try journaling or start a blog ♪

16:27.666 --> 16:31.625
♪ Just end this inner monologue ♪

16:31.708 --> 16:33.583
♪ Seethe if you must ♪

16:33.666 --> 16:36.666
♪ But just breathe ♪

16:36.750 --> 16:39.625
Okay. I just got off the phone
with the state's attorney.

16:39.708 --> 16:43.625
She thinks this is a civil rights issue.
This is a big deal, Emma.

16:43.708 --> 16:45.041
So, what are you saying?

16:45.125 --> 16:48.208
I'm just saying I'm really excited
to be a part of something like this.

16:48.291 --> 16:50.166
We'll see how the PTA meeting goes.

16:50.250 --> 16:52.791
Well, it's not gonna be fun.
We'll get through it.

16:52.875 --> 16:54.708
Just take a sec. Relax.

16:54.791 --> 16:56.875
[bell rings]

17:00.416 --> 17:03.291
♪ Just breathe, Emma ♪

17:03.375 --> 17:05.875
♪ Remember that thing called oxygen ♪

17:05.958 --> 17:09.041
♪ Just breathe, Emma ♪

17:09.125 --> 17:11.333
♪ Look at the crazy state you're in ♪

17:11.416 --> 17:14.500
♪ Just smile and nod
Although they're jerks ♪

17:14.583 --> 17:18.333
♪ Say "namaste" and pray it works ♪

17:18.416 --> 17:21.708
♪ And like we've discussed ♪

17:22.833 --> 17:24.041
♪ Just… ♪

17:24.958 --> 17:31.833
♪ Breathe ♪

17:34.625 --> 17:36.208
[bell rings]

17:37.541 --> 17:41.125
[choir] ♪ When wilt thou
Save the people? ♪

17:41.208 --> 17:43.416
-Blue one. Blue.
-This stop motion sickness?

17:43.500 --> 17:44.916
Mmm-hmm, and everything else.

17:45.000 --> 17:46.208
[choir] ♪ The people… ♪

17:46.291 --> 17:48.000
[Barry] Okay. Enough! Enough!

17:48.083 --> 17:50.833
Stop singing, stop!
You're making me hate God.

17:50.916 --> 17:53.416
-[Angie] You're scaring them.
-They're scaring me.

17:53.500 --> 17:55.416
How about we do some trust exercises?

17:55.500 --> 17:57.833
-[choir murmuring indistinctly]
-Yeah? Good.

17:57.916 --> 18:02.833
Hotel is booked. Breakfast isn't included,
but there is a Waffle Shed next door.

18:02.916 --> 18:04.750
-Sounds delicious.
-[Angie] Mmm-hmm.

18:04.833 --> 18:09.083
We're doing a great thing here.
We're being great people.

18:09.166 --> 18:10.958
This is all great. [chuckles]

18:12.083 --> 18:14.750
This is gonna get me my third Tony Award.

18:14.833 --> 18:17.083
-[scoffs] Oh, my God.
-What?

18:17.958 --> 18:22.000
Oh, come on, you know
how political the Tonys are.

18:22.083 --> 18:25.041
They don't vote for you.
They vote for your brand.

18:25.125 --> 18:28.208
My brand is
a little tarnished at the moment.

18:28.291 --> 18:30.708
'Cause of the infamous tirade
at the Longacre Theatre?

18:30.791 --> 18:34.083
When a cell phone goes off
in the middle of a performance…

18:34.166 --> 18:36.291
-I can't be held responsible.
-It was your cell phone!

18:36.375 --> 18:38.958
-I didn't know that!
-It was in your wig!

18:39.041 --> 18:41.375
I didn't know that at the time. Anyway…

18:42.041 --> 18:47.291
All the goodwill that we're gonna get
from this thing will wash me clean,

18:47.375 --> 18:51.333
and I will win, no matter what
my next project is. [chuckles]

18:51.416 --> 18:54.291
You're just greedy.
I'd be happy with one Tony.

18:54.375 --> 18:57.458
-I thought I had a shot with FDR.
-Mmm-hmm.

18:57.541 --> 18:59.208
I need a win.

18:59.291 --> 19:02.833
I'm so sick of all the rejection.
I'm no Dee Dee Allen.

19:02.916 --> 19:05.541
-A lot of bile.
-Well, I'm angry at life.

19:05.625 --> 19:07.958
No, I mean Trent. He's retching again.

19:08.625 --> 19:11.333
You were saying something about your…

19:12.000 --> 19:14.625
I got into this business,
yes, because I loved it,

19:14.708 --> 19:17.875
but also to prove
to everyone who doubted me,

19:17.958 --> 19:23.375
my… teachers, the kids
on the school bus, my horrible parents,

19:23.458 --> 19:26.000
that I could do something.
Something important.

19:26.625 --> 19:29.875
[exhales]
That's exactly what we are doing.

19:30.500 --> 19:32.208
Something important.

19:33.375 --> 19:35.416
I just hope we don't screw it up.

19:37.666 --> 19:38.958
[Angie] Hit it.

19:39.041 --> 19:40.666
♪ Day by day… ♪

19:40.750 --> 19:44.083
♪ Day by day ♪

19:44.166 --> 19:48.000
♪ Day by day ♪

19:48.083 --> 19:49.791
♪ Three things I pray ♪

19:49.875 --> 19:51.750
-♪ Three things I pray ♪
-[retches]

19:51.833 --> 19:55.291
I'm sorry, you're telling us
that the state's attorney

19:55.375 --> 19:57.875
is forcing us to have a prom?

19:57.958 --> 20:01.875
No, the state's attorney
wants us to hold an inclusive prom.

20:01.958 --> 20:03.333
-Yes.
-[audience murmurs]

20:03.416 --> 20:06.875
Because that's what they feel
best reflects America's values.

20:06.958 --> 20:10.208
Well, this isn't America. This is Indiana.

20:10.291 --> 20:11.583
[audience applauds]

20:11.666 --> 20:12.708
All right.

20:16.208 --> 20:19.000
Just to be clear, this is America

20:19.083 --> 20:22.458
and everyone gets to have an opinion--
Oh, just like you.

20:22.541 --> 20:23.958
[microphone feedback squeals]

20:27.041 --> 20:29.666
My son will not be forced
to go to a homosexual prom.

20:29.750 --> 20:30.916
[audience applauds]

20:31.000 --> 20:34.083
Thank you, Beverly! Thank you!

20:34.166 --> 20:37.666
Again, it is not a homosexual prom.
It is an inclusive prom…

20:37.750 --> 20:40.083
-With homosexuals.
-You don't have to attend--

20:40.625 --> 20:43.083
You don't have to attend
if you don't want to.

20:43.166 --> 20:46.833
Look… I… I'm sorry you're upset,

20:46.916 --> 20:51.125
but the organization of the prom is
within the purview of the student council.

20:51.208 --> 20:54.291
Let's hear what they have to say. Alyssa?

20:54.375 --> 20:56.916
-Uh… Okay.
-[scattered applause]

20:57.000 --> 20:58.083
[feedback whines]

20:58.666 --> 21:01.833
Well, we want prom to go on, obviously.

21:04.125 --> 21:07.375
It's supposed to be
a celebration of all students--

21:07.458 --> 21:09.458
Okay. No, thank you. It's fine, everyone.

21:09.541 --> 21:14.208
Sweetheart, I'm so sorry,
but this is not a student matter.

21:14.291 --> 21:19.750
This is about government…
tearing our community apart.

21:19.833 --> 21:20.666
[audience cheering]

21:20.750 --> 21:24.750
It's about big government
taking away our freedom of choice.

21:24.833 --> 21:26.208
[Principal Hawkins] Okay. Okay.

21:26.291 --> 21:29.083
This is not about government intervention.

21:29.166 --> 21:31.000
Emma, what is this about?

21:32.375 --> 21:34.583
I just want to go to prom
like any other kid.

21:34.666 --> 21:37.041
[Principal Hawkins]
Mmm-hmm. But you can't.

21:37.125 --> 21:40.083
She can't, and that's why
the courts are involved.

21:40.166 --> 21:41.375
Ask yourself.

21:42.250 --> 21:46.125
What exactly is it that you find
so frightening about gay people?

21:46.208 --> 21:48.875
-[door crashes opens]
-[Barry] Hold it! Stop! Stop!

21:48.958 --> 21:50.125
Hold it!

21:50.208 --> 21:53.833
-[indistinct chatter]
-What you are doing here is wrong.

21:54.458 --> 21:56.416
I'm sorry. Who are you?

21:56.500 --> 21:59.250
Where is our girl? Where's Emma? Emma!

21:59.333 --> 22:00.708
I'm Emma.

22:00.791 --> 22:05.750
Emma, my name is Barry, and I'm here
to tell you that you are not alone.

22:05.833 --> 22:09.250
Okay? I am as gay as a bucket of wigs.

22:09.333 --> 22:11.416
-[audience clamoring]
-[loudly] A bucket of them!

22:11.500 --> 22:14.583
And we are here from New York City
and we are gonna save you.

22:14.666 --> 22:16.333
Tomorrow, we will hold a rally.

22:16.416 --> 22:19.333
-There'll be banners and choreography.
-Excuse me.

22:19.416 --> 22:22.541
-Excuse me!
-[Barry] Shame! Shame!

22:22.625 --> 22:25.125
[loudly] Excuse me!

22:25.708 --> 22:26.625
[exhales sharply]

22:27.208 --> 22:30.416
What is going on? Who are you people?

22:30.500 --> 22:32.250
We are liberals from Broadway.

22:32.333 --> 22:33.416
[indistinct chatter]

22:33.500 --> 22:34.625
Oh, shut up!

22:34.708 --> 22:38.458
We are here to open
your hearts and your minds.

22:38.541 --> 22:41.250
The five of us are gonna teach you…

22:41.833 --> 22:43.291
-Where's Dee Dee?
-You'll see.

22:44.833 --> 22:46.583
-All right.
-[intense music playing]

22:50.250 --> 22:52.708
Oh, my God. That's Dee Dee Allen.

22:52.791 --> 22:57.166
♪ I want to tell the people of… ♪

22:58.000 --> 23:00.208
♪ Whatever this town's called ♪

23:01.708 --> 23:04.416
♪ I know what's going on here ♪

23:04.500 --> 23:07.875
♪ And frankly, I'm appalled ♪

23:08.500 --> 23:13.583
♪ I read three quarters of a news story
And knew I had to come ♪

23:13.666 --> 23:19.833
♪ And unless I am doing
The Miracle Worker ♪

23:22.125 --> 23:25.250
♪ I… ♪

23:25.333 --> 23:28.833
♪ Won't play blind ♪

23:28.916 --> 23:32.708
♪ Deaf and dumb ♪

23:34.833 --> 23:37.125
♪ Listen, you bigoted monsters ♪

23:37.208 --> 23:39.875
♪ Just who do you think you are? ♪

23:39.958 --> 23:42.416
♪ Your prejudice and your oppression ♪

23:42.500 --> 23:45.625
♪ Won't get past this Broadway star ♪

23:45.708 --> 23:50.875
♪ Stealing the rights of a girl
Who is an LGBQ teen ♪

23:50.958 --> 23:55.583
♪ I've been far too angry to google
What those letters mean ♪

23:56.583 --> 24:01.833
♪ But it's not about me,
It's about poor… ♪

24:01.916 --> 24:06.125
-Emma!
-♪ Emma, for can't you see ♪

24:06.208 --> 24:08.458
♪ The raw deal she's been dealt? ♪

24:09.041 --> 24:12.000
♪ So hear my plea ♪

24:12.083 --> 24:14.875
♪ Or here's your next dilemma ♪

24:15.500 --> 24:18.541
♪ How do you silence a woman
Who's known for her belt? ♪

24:18.625 --> 24:19.750
Sing it, Eleanor!

24:20.875 --> 24:24.458
♪ Her belt! ♪

24:24.541 --> 24:26.125
♪ But it's not about me ♪

24:26.208 --> 24:28.250
Get them out of here now!

24:28.333 --> 24:30.333
♪ Go on and threaten to riot ♪

24:30.416 --> 24:32.791
♪ It won't faze me in the least ♪

24:33.541 --> 24:35.958
♪ I understand furious townsfolk ♪

24:36.041 --> 24:38.708
♪ I did Beauty and the Beast ♪

24:38.791 --> 24:41.000
♪ I'm no stranger to slander ♪

24:41.083 --> 24:44.375
♪ So, my dear, you're not alone ♪

24:44.458 --> 24:48.916
♪ The Post once said
I was too old to play Eva Perón ♪

24:49.000 --> 24:50.125
No.

24:50.208 --> 24:53.416
♪ Eva Perón! ♪

24:53.500 --> 24:56.250
♪ But it is not about me ♪

24:56.333 --> 24:59.250
♪ It's Emma's story, damn it! ♪

24:59.333 --> 25:02.416
♪ Equality ♪

25:02.500 --> 25:05.166
♪ Should be this country's norm ♪

25:05.250 --> 25:08.541
♪ No photography ♪

25:08.625 --> 25:11.041
♪ Unless you Instagram it ♪

25:11.583 --> 25:15.166
♪ Use hashtag Dee Dee
Takes Local Yokels by Storm ♪

25:16.416 --> 25:18.083
♪ But it's not about me ♪

25:18.166 --> 25:19.166
[chuckles] That's cute.

25:19.250 --> 25:21.708
♪ I didn't come here to make a scene ♪

25:21.791 --> 25:24.208
♪ But I know how Emma's heart aches ♪

25:24.791 --> 25:27.416
♪ And this is how actors intervene ♪

25:27.500 --> 25:29.750
♪ With fiery songs and dance breaks ♪

25:32.500 --> 25:33.833
[yelps]

25:49.875 --> 25:52.916
♪ But it's not about me ♪

25:53.000 --> 25:55.875
♪ Although I'm rich and famous ♪

25:55.958 --> 26:00.875
♪ Publicity is not my final goal ♪

26:00.958 --> 26:02.375
♪ Call security! ♪

26:02.458 --> 26:08.000
♪ You needn't be
Some backwoods ignoramus ♪

26:08.083 --> 26:10.375
♪ Join me and we'll start fighting ♪

26:10.458 --> 26:12.291
♪ Could I get softer lighting? ♪

26:12.375 --> 26:14.541
♪ Wait, this is… ♪

26:14.625 --> 26:20.041
-♪ Not… ♪
-♪ Not… ♪

26:20.125 --> 26:21.916
-♪ About me! ♪
-♪ This is not about… ♪

26:22.000 --> 26:24.541
-♪ What is happening? ♪
-♪ This is not about… ♪

26:24.625 --> 26:25.791
♪ What is happening? ♪

26:25.875 --> 26:27.250
♪ This is not about… ♪

26:29.000 --> 26:31.291
♪ It is all about, uh, Emma ♪

26:31.375 --> 26:34.083
♪ And not about… ♪

26:34.708 --> 26:39.583
♪ Me! ♪

26:42.666 --> 26:45.291
Who was responsible for that? Was it you?

26:45.375 --> 26:48.375
Me? No, I have no idea
what just happened in there.

26:48.458 --> 26:52.375
Strangers burst in hurling insults
at the parents, and you do nothing.

26:52.458 --> 26:54.791
What kind of school
are you running here, Mr. Hawkins?

26:54.875 --> 26:56.583
[sighs]

27:01.333 --> 27:04.083
Excuse me, Miss Allen.
I'm Tom. Tom Hawkins.

27:04.166 --> 27:08.333
I am the principal and I just, um…
What are you doing?

27:08.416 --> 27:10.583
We have come to show this community

27:10.666 --> 27:14.208
that gay people
and gay-positive icons, such as myself,

27:14.291 --> 27:16.791
[inhales] are made of the same
flesh and blood as they are.

27:16.875 --> 27:17.750
Uh-huh.

27:17.833 --> 27:21.833
If they don't have gay people here,
why is my Scruff going crazy right now?

27:21.916 --> 27:23.333
We're not monsters.

27:24.083 --> 27:26.291
We're cultural disruptors. [chuckles]

27:27.250 --> 27:28.250
I'm a fan.

27:31.666 --> 27:35.083
-Really?
-Yeah. Yes, I am. [giggles]

27:35.166 --> 27:36.000
[gasps]

27:36.708 --> 27:41.583
[chuckles] What kind of a fan?
Big fan? Small fan? Scary stabby fan?

27:41.666 --> 27:44.125
You could say that I'm a big fan. Yes.

27:44.208 --> 27:48.916
Really? That's so surprising
because you're not my usual demographic.

27:49.000 --> 27:51.000
-You mean Black?
-No, straight.

27:52.166 --> 27:54.041
You are straight, right?

27:54.125 --> 27:57.250
Yes. I am.
Straight people like Broadway too.

27:57.333 --> 28:01.208
[chuckles] I've heard that.
Always thought it was a fairy tale.

28:01.291 --> 28:05.500
-[chuckles] So to speak.
-[chuckles] So to speak. Well, it's true.

28:05.583 --> 28:07.541
Um, I've been a fan since I saw you

28:07.625 --> 28:09.541
in the show for which
you won your first Tony.

28:09.625 --> 28:12.583
-No! You saw Swallow the Moon?
-I did.

28:12.666 --> 28:16.958
The number at the top of the second act,
"The Lady's Improving"? Chills.

28:17.041 --> 28:19.833
[chuckles] That song made me a star.

28:19.916 --> 28:21.375
It made me a fan.

28:21.458 --> 28:24.125
-Uh, Dee Dee, we gotta make haste.
-Okay.

28:24.208 --> 28:26.958
Uh, Miss Allen, I just…
This is a very delicate situation.

28:27.041 --> 28:29.958
I'm asking you and your friends
to back off for a few days.

28:30.458 --> 28:32.291
-Back off?
-Yeah.

28:32.916 --> 28:35.416
Backing off
is exactly what we're not going to do.

28:35.500 --> 28:39.500
I see what's happening here.
You're trying to disarm me with flattery.

28:39.583 --> 28:43.666
It's not going to work, Tom.
Flattery makes me stronger.

28:43.750 --> 28:45.625
Fuels my ego.

29:03.625 --> 29:06.541
-[Alyssa] That was insane.
-I know.

29:06.625 --> 29:08.958
-I'm really freaking out.
-Don't freak out.

29:09.041 --> 29:10.916
We have a plan, remember?

29:11.000 --> 29:13.416
We're gonna get dressed up and go to prom

29:13.500 --> 29:17.250
and be together in public,
not hide anymore.

29:17.875 --> 29:19.166
Are you sure about this?

29:19.958 --> 29:22.250
There's only one thing I'm sure about.

29:23.125 --> 29:25.958
♪ I don't want to start a riot ♪

29:26.041 --> 29:29.000
♪ I don't want to blaze a trail ♪

29:29.083 --> 29:32.541
♪ I don't want to be a symbol ♪

29:32.625 --> 29:35.583
♪ Or a cautionary tale ♪

29:35.666 --> 29:38.750
♪ I don't want to be a scapegoat ♪

29:38.833 --> 29:42.250
♪ For people to oppose ♪

29:42.333 --> 29:45.416
♪ What I want is simple ♪

29:45.500 --> 29:50.708
♪ As far as wanting goes ♪

29:50.791 --> 29:55.416
♪ I just want to dance with you ♪

29:55.500 --> 29:58.291
-♪ Let the whole world melt away ♪
-[laughing]

29:58.375 --> 30:01.458
♪ And dance with you ♪

30:01.541 --> 30:04.208
♪ Who cares what other people say? ♪

30:04.291 --> 30:07.541
♪ And when we're through ♪

30:07.625 --> 30:10.250
♪ No one can convince us ♪

30:10.333 --> 30:13.583
♪ We were wrong ♪

30:13.666 --> 30:18.000
♪ All it takes is you and me ♪

30:18.083 --> 30:22.500
♪ And a song ♪

30:23.291 --> 30:24.333
[Alyssa laughs]

30:25.416 --> 30:28.291
♪ I don't need a big production ♪

30:28.375 --> 30:31.000
♪ Streamers hanging in the air ♪

30:31.083 --> 30:34.291
♪ I don't need to spend the night with ♪

30:34.375 --> 30:37.125
♪ Confetti in my hair ♪

30:37.208 --> 30:40.250
-[laughing]
-♪ I don't need a room of people ♪

30:40.333 --> 30:43.875
♪ That I don't really know ♪

30:43.958 --> 30:46.166
♪ I just want to hold you ♪

30:46.250 --> 30:50.666
♪ And never let you go! ♪

30:50.750 --> 30:55.333
♪ I just want to dance with you ♪

30:55.416 --> 30:58.125
♪ Let the whole world melt away ♪

30:58.208 --> 31:01.125
♪ And dance with you ♪

31:01.208 --> 31:03.875
♪ Who cares what other people say? ♪

31:03.958 --> 31:07.250
♪ And when we're through… ♪

31:07.333 --> 31:09.791
♪ No one can convince us ♪

31:09.875 --> 31:12.833
♪ We were wrong ♪

31:12.916 --> 31:17.291
♪ All it takes is you and me ♪

31:17.875 --> 31:21.000
♪ And a song ♪

31:21.750 --> 31:22.750
[car honks]

31:22.833 --> 31:25.250
It's my mom. I gotta go.

31:26.083 --> 31:27.083
Okay.

31:29.000 --> 31:29.833
Bye…

31:32.750 --> 31:37.083
♪ All it takes is you and me ♪

31:37.833 --> 31:40.125
♪ And… ♪

31:40.208 --> 31:45.833
♪ A song ♪

31:54.750 --> 31:56.541
[Dee Dee groans] Oh, God.

31:57.250 --> 31:58.083
[groans]

31:58.791 --> 32:00.416
It's worse than the bus.

32:01.125 --> 32:03.458
[Angie] At least it's quieter. Huh?

32:04.041 --> 32:06.333
I need a drink. [exhales]

32:06.416 --> 32:08.125
-[bell dings]
-Hello?

32:09.958 --> 32:13.458
Oh. Dickinson, four rooms.
I called yesterday.

32:13.541 --> 32:15.625
Four rooms of varying size

32:15.708 --> 32:18.500
to reflect the hierarchy
of the company, right? [chuckles]

32:19.541 --> 32:21.083
Where is my suite?

32:21.750 --> 32:23.250
We don't have a suite.

32:28.083 --> 32:30.166
-Now do you have a suite?
-Oh!

32:30.916 --> 32:34.166
No, we don't have any suites.
All the rooms are the same.

32:34.250 --> 32:36.416
-[Dee Dee sighs]
-[Angie] Oh!

32:36.500 --> 32:37.958
Surely you know who I am.

32:38.041 --> 32:41.291
At the very least,
I would like a room next to the spa.

32:41.375 --> 32:43.166
Uh, there's no spa.

32:43.750 --> 32:46.958
Angie, what is this place?
We're all gonna get stabbed and stuffed.

32:47.041 --> 32:49.583
-You know that, right?
-Orbitz gave it three stars!

32:49.666 --> 32:50.500
[sighs]

32:51.750 --> 32:54.041
Do you have any cabins?

32:54.666 --> 32:56.375
No, we don't have any cabins.

33:04.958 --> 33:07.416
-How about now?
-[laughing] What is that?

33:07.500 --> 33:09.750
It's a Drama Desk. You know what it is.

33:10.416 --> 33:13.208
-[whispering] I vomited in the bus again.
-[Angie] Mmm.

33:13.291 --> 33:15.125
Can I see the hotel doctor, please?

33:15.208 --> 33:16.958
Oh, my God, it's you.

33:17.041 --> 33:19.541
I can't believe it. It's actually you.

33:19.625 --> 33:22.875
You're the guy from Talk to the Hand.
It's on every night at 9:00 after--

33:22.958 --> 33:26.541
-Can I have my room, please?
-Okay, let's get started. All right?

33:26.625 --> 33:28.750
-Let's change some minds.
-[Angie] Uh…

33:28.833 --> 33:29.958
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

33:30.041 --> 33:32.458
-[Angie] Oh! A wishing well!
-[Dee Dee gasps]

33:32.541 --> 33:34.333
Make a wish, Dee Dee.

33:34.416 --> 33:36.041
Death. I wish for death.

33:36.125 --> 33:40.041
Okay, Sheldon's working on a venue.
Now, how's the song?

33:40.125 --> 33:44.833
Uh, about that.
I was misled by my representation.

33:44.916 --> 33:48.625
Mr. Sondheim is not a fan
of my Sweeney Todd.

33:48.708 --> 33:51.208
-Quite the opposite, actually.
-[Barry] Oh, my God…

33:51.291 --> 33:54.125
Jesus, Trent, you screwed us.

33:54.208 --> 33:58.625
Don't worry.
I wrote something myself. Yeah.

34:00.833 --> 34:02.958
It's quite rousing,

34:03.041 --> 34:05.958
and in a very humane key.

34:06.041 --> 34:08.375
The Godspell kids will back us up,

34:08.458 --> 34:11.625
and they have their own costumes.
You're welcome.

34:13.208 --> 34:16.166
-Oh, my God. [giggles]
-Yeah!

34:16.250 --> 34:18.125
-This is awful.
-[giggles]

34:18.208 --> 34:20.500
We can't perform this.
They'll boo us off the stage.

34:20.583 --> 34:24.041
No, all we need is a simple message
that tugs at the heartstrings

34:24.125 --> 34:25.333
and a little pageantry.

34:25.416 --> 34:28.625
-We have everything we need right here.
-Except a venue.

34:28.708 --> 34:30.666
O ye of little faith.

34:31.250 --> 34:35.375
[chuckles] I got one!
And a crowd of 2,500 guaranteed.

34:35.458 --> 34:38.083
-What?
-That's amazing!

34:38.166 --> 34:40.541
What is it? One of those
beautiful Antebellum theaters?

34:40.625 --> 34:42.458
No, it's, uh…

34:43.208 --> 34:44.208
an arena.

34:46.000 --> 34:47.500
An arena?

34:48.333 --> 34:50.625
-[engines roaring]
-[loud rock music playing]

35:03.458 --> 35:05.291
So it's come to this.

35:09.875 --> 35:11.583
[engine revving]

35:15.958 --> 35:17.666
[announcer] Ladies and gentlemen,

35:18.500 --> 35:22.291
Truckosaurus,
the car-eating robot dinosaur,

35:22.375 --> 35:25.333
will not be your
half-time entertainment today.

35:25.416 --> 35:28.458
Instead, we have some guests
who've come from New York

35:28.541 --> 35:30.666
to sing us a song about intolerance.

35:30.750 --> 35:32.250
-[crowd jeering]
-Hi there.

35:32.333 --> 35:36.208
I'm Trent Oliver, actor, activist…

35:37.125 --> 35:38.875
and Juilliard graduate.

35:38.958 --> 35:41.625
Emma, this one's for you.

35:41.708 --> 35:44.125
[instrumental music playing]

35:47.916 --> 35:52.708
♪ Flowers accept the rain
And grow more beautiful ♪

35:54.208 --> 35:57.041
♪ Babies accept their mother's breast ♪

35:57.125 --> 35:59.625
♪ So they can grow strong ♪

36:00.500 --> 36:05.041
♪ I accept that I was born
A handsome man ♪

36:05.500 --> 36:06.625
[man boos]

36:06.708 --> 36:11.833
♪ So join with me
And sing this acceptance song ♪

36:11.916 --> 36:15.833
♪ Let us accept one another ♪

36:15.916 --> 36:18.458
♪ I know it's truly hard ♪

36:19.541 --> 36:22.208
♪ We're sister and brother ♪

36:22.291 --> 36:25.583
♪ Here's what I learned at Juilliard ♪

36:25.666 --> 36:28.708
-[audience booing]
-♪ Bigotry's not big of me ♪

36:28.791 --> 36:31.375
♪ And it's not big of you ♪

36:32.083 --> 36:34.833
♪ Let's all work together ♪

36:34.916 --> 36:39.416
♪ To make rainbow dreams come true ♪

36:39.500 --> 36:43.541
[announcer] Ladies and gentlemen, two-time
Tony Award winner, Miss Dee Dee Allen.

36:43.625 --> 36:47.000
-Trent, I could rip your face off.
-I'm sorry.

36:47.083 --> 36:49.833
[Barry] You made me fail.
I am so sick of failing.

36:49.916 --> 36:51.250
What do we do now?

36:51.333 --> 36:52.375
We leave.

36:52.958 --> 36:56.291
-First we kill Trent, then we leave.
-What about the girl?

36:56.375 --> 36:58.583
-[Dee Dee sighs]
-[Principal Hawkins] Hello, everyone…

36:59.791 --> 37:03.458
We have some news. Emma and I
wanted to be the ones to tell you,

37:03.541 --> 37:07.750
thanks to pressure from the state's
attorney's office, prom is back on!

37:07.833 --> 37:09.708
-[Barry] What?
-Prom is back on! [squeals]

37:09.791 --> 37:11.666
-[all cheering]
-We did it!

37:11.750 --> 37:12.625
Yay!

37:12.708 --> 37:16.041
See? We're not narcissists.

37:16.125 --> 37:18.416
Just to be clear, uh,
it's not because of you…

37:18.500 --> 37:19.708
Well, maybe it was.

37:19.791 --> 37:23.000
I mean, everybody started freaking out
when you got here.

37:23.083 --> 37:26.791
The lawyer might've had legal power,
but you really scared people.

37:26.875 --> 37:28.208
-[Angie] Aw!
-We scared people!

37:28.291 --> 37:29.958
Important thing is, it's a victory.

37:30.041 --> 37:31.916
Now you get to go to prom
like everybody else!

37:32.000 --> 37:34.125
-[Angie] Yes!
-What are you gonna wear?

37:34.208 --> 37:38.041
I was thinking like a vintage tux
and some high tops.

37:38.125 --> 37:40.083
I don't know. Does it matter?

37:41.750 --> 37:42.750
-Does it…
-[scoffs]

37:43.541 --> 37:44.875
[snickers]

37:45.875 --> 37:49.166
-Honey…
-Sweetheart, boo-boo.

37:49.250 --> 37:51.625
I don't know you, okay?
And you don't know me,

37:51.708 --> 37:56.083
but I am begging you,
let me dress you for the prom.

37:56.166 --> 37:57.750
-Okay? Yeah?
-Okay.

37:57.833 --> 37:59.625
We're going to Saks.

37:59.708 --> 38:02.166
-Uh, there's no Saks here.
-We have a Kmart!

38:02.250 --> 38:03.958
-A what?
-A Kmart.

38:06.208 --> 38:08.208
-[laughs]
-[Barry] Fine.

38:09.166 --> 38:11.791
We'll check out
the Reba McEntire collection at Kmart,

38:11.875 --> 38:12.916
do a little fashion show.

38:13.000 --> 38:16.625
Okay! Oh, can we do it tomorrow?
We can meet at my place.

38:16.708 --> 38:18.875
I have to go and find out
if I still have a date.

38:18.958 --> 38:20.875
Sure. I'll go ahead, do a pre-shop.

38:20.958 --> 38:23.458
Okay? Will you give me a ride
in your pickup truck?

38:23.541 --> 38:26.166
Are you saying that because I'm a lesbian,
I drive a pickup?

38:26.250 --> 38:28.708
-Well, do you? [chuckles]
-Shut up.

38:28.791 --> 38:30.791
-[Sheldon] Anybody hungry?
-[Angie] I could drink.

38:30.875 --> 38:33.916
-[Sheldon] What's around here?
-I saw a Big Boy by the highway.

38:34.000 --> 38:37.208
-[Sheldon] Ooh, they have a gay bar here?
-[Angie] I love Big Boy.

38:37.291 --> 38:40.625
Oh, gay bar. Can't go. I'd be mobbed.

38:40.708 --> 38:42.208
-Oh! Of course.
-[both chuckle]

38:46.541 --> 38:49.166
-So, it's nice to see Emma smile again.
-Yes.

38:49.250 --> 38:50.875
She's had a rough go of it.

38:50.958 --> 38:53.416
I gathered that. Yeah.

38:53.500 --> 38:56.166
-Even before the prom controversy.
-Oh?

38:56.250 --> 39:00.375
When she came out, her parents,
well, they threw her out of the house.

39:01.750 --> 39:04.916
-Really?
-Yeah. Yeah. She was 16.

39:05.541 --> 39:07.458
-It was, uh, pretty ugly.
-Oh…

39:10.333 --> 39:12.000
Anyway, um…

39:12.916 --> 39:14.458
thank you for helping her…

39:15.625 --> 39:18.166
-Or trying to.
-[both chuckle softly]

39:18.958 --> 39:20.125
[Dee Dee] Yeah…

39:23.833 --> 39:25.791
-Uh, Tom?
-Yes, yeah?

39:26.583 --> 39:31.000
Is there a restaurant in town
that has plates and cutlery and…

39:31.083 --> 39:33.833
Oh, uh, there's an Applebee's by the mall.

39:33.916 --> 39:34.750
[gasps]

39:37.583 --> 39:39.000
-Would you like to go?
-Yes.

39:39.083 --> 39:42.666
Take me now to this Apples & Bees place.

39:42.750 --> 39:43.666
-[giggles]
-All right.

39:43.750 --> 39:45.416
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

39:45.500 --> 39:46.750
How nice of you.

39:47.541 --> 39:49.291
[indistinct chatter and laughter]

39:49.833 --> 39:52.000
-Guess what today is?
-What?

39:52.083 --> 39:53.541
Promposal day!

39:53.625 --> 39:54.625
[boy 1] Hey, Kaylee!

39:59.041 --> 40:00.083
[all gasp]

40:00.625 --> 40:04.291
♪ Since JV football, I've been adored ♪

40:04.375 --> 40:07.458
♪ Big man on campus but oh-so-bored ♪

40:07.541 --> 40:09.833
♪ My life was perfect ♪

40:09.916 --> 40:11.375
♪ But so routine ♪

40:11.458 --> 40:16.291
♪ I prayed for someone to intervene ♪

40:16.375 --> 40:20.500
♪ Then something new happened ♪

40:20.583 --> 40:23.500
♪ And turned my life around entirely ♪

40:23.583 --> 40:27.750
♪ And that's 'cause you happened ♪

40:27.833 --> 40:30.791
♪ And look what happened to me ♪

40:31.583 --> 40:34.166
♪ So go to prom with me, Kaylee! ♪

40:34.250 --> 40:36.750
-You're such an idiot. Yes!
-[boy 1] Whoo!

40:37.916 --> 40:39.500
[boy 2] Hey, Shelby, you're next.

40:41.291 --> 40:44.500
♪ There's not one subject
That I could pass ♪

40:45.083 --> 40:48.541
♪ Before you walked into
My Spanish class ♪

40:48.625 --> 40:50.000
♪ Was my heart pounding? ♪

40:50.583 --> 40:51.708
♪ I won't say no ♪

40:51.791 --> 40:56.333
♪ 'Cause life without you was no bueno ♪

40:57.041 --> 41:00.750
♪ Then something new happened ♪

41:00.833 --> 41:04.250
♪ And turned my life around entirely ♪

41:04.333 --> 41:08.333
♪ And that's 'cause you happened ♪

41:08.416 --> 41:11.250
♪ And look what happened to me ♪

41:12.125 --> 41:14.708
♪ So go to prom with me, Shelby! ♪

41:14.791 --> 41:16.416
Sí! Sí, señor!

41:17.083 --> 41:17.916
[all cheering]

41:22.541 --> 41:25.666
[Alyssa] You did it.
No, you actually did it.

41:25.750 --> 41:27.583
We have a prom because of you.

41:27.666 --> 41:31.375
It's like a love bomb went off.
I've seen six promposals today.

41:31.458 --> 41:34.708
People are gonna see us
dancing together and kissing.

41:34.791 --> 41:37.125
It's gonna be impossible not to kiss you.

41:37.708 --> 41:41.041
Oh, my God, and you know,
what's my mom going to think?

41:41.125 --> 41:44.000
I mean, she'll be in public,
so she can't totally freak out.

41:44.083 --> 41:48.291
It doesn't matter what she does.
This is about us.

41:48.875 --> 41:52.208
This is about us finally being us.

41:52.791 --> 41:57.125
♪ And no more hiding how we feel anymore ♪

41:57.208 --> 42:00.208
♪ I won't hide if you're by my side ♪

42:00.291 --> 42:02.708
♪ Now that the prom is back ♪

42:02.791 --> 42:06.958
♪ On track ♪

42:07.541 --> 42:11.125
♪ And once we walk into that gym ♪

42:11.208 --> 42:14.875
♪ Hand-in-hand ♪

42:14.958 --> 42:17.458
♪ It's pretty obvious ♪

42:17.541 --> 42:20.000
♪ There's no going back ♪

42:20.083 --> 42:22.041
♪ And that's a promise ♪

42:27.541 --> 42:29.500
[Dee Dee and Principal Hawkins laughing]

42:29.583 --> 42:32.625
I save all of my money.
I go to New York every summer.

42:32.708 --> 42:34.958
-I see as many Broadway shows as I can.
-Oh.

42:35.041 --> 42:37.041
When I run out of money,
I second act them.

42:37.125 --> 42:38.833
-Oh.
-Don't tell anybody.

42:38.916 --> 42:40.666
-Bad!
-[both chuckle]

42:41.458 --> 42:44.916
My point is,
I've seen you many, many times.

42:45.000 --> 42:46.208
Oh.

42:46.291 --> 42:47.916
Mr. Hawkins.

42:49.000 --> 42:50.291
Mrs. Greene.

42:50.375 --> 42:52.041
Hello. I'm Dee Dee Allen.

42:52.125 --> 42:53.875
-We haven't officially met.
-No.

42:53.958 --> 42:56.250
-Hello. Dee Dee Allen.
-We're aware.

42:57.833 --> 43:03.083
Ms. Allen, I'm sure that you are
very well-versed in the ways of the world

43:03.166 --> 43:06.125
and Broadway in particular.
That's a community.

43:07.000 --> 43:11.000
But you don't know us.
You don't know this town and our values.

43:12.000 --> 43:15.625
No, well, I'm just here
advocating on behalf of a young girl

43:15.708 --> 43:20.333
whose voice perhaps is not heard
by some in the community.

43:20.916 --> 43:26.458
Yes. Well, perhaps you should stick
to acting instead of activism.

43:28.500 --> 43:29.708
Enjoy your meal.

43:33.000 --> 43:33.833
[smacks lips]

43:34.708 --> 43:37.291
We didn't mean
to make anything worse here.

43:37.375 --> 43:39.250
I appreciate everything that you're doing.

43:40.583 --> 43:42.125
Well, let's just drop it.

43:42.208 --> 43:43.041
Yeah.

43:43.875 --> 43:45.458
Tell me… [chuckles softly]

43:46.083 --> 43:48.333
I've never said this before to anyone.

43:49.375 --> 43:50.791
Tell me about you.

43:52.125 --> 43:54.000
-About me?
-Yeah.

43:56.000 --> 43:58.958
I don't know.
I'm just a small-town principal.

43:59.833 --> 44:05.083
Uh, you know, it can be frustrating,
but, uh, at least I have a job.

44:05.166 --> 44:06.458
Yeah, lucky you.

44:06.541 --> 44:07.416
Single.

44:08.708 --> 44:09.541
Sorry?

44:10.250 --> 44:12.500
I'm single. Just putting that out there.

44:13.083 --> 44:14.833
Really? [giggles]

44:16.416 --> 44:18.625
I'm surprised.

44:18.708 --> 44:21.000
Oh, well, I'm surprised you're surprised.

44:21.083 --> 44:23.625
[chuckles] The two things
I'm most passionate about in the world

44:23.708 --> 44:26.291
are Broadway musicals
and secondary school administration.

44:26.375 --> 44:27.291
Oh.

44:27.375 --> 44:31.958
I typed that into a dating website once,
and a little message popped up that said,

44:32.041 --> 44:34.125
"You will have zero matches forever."

44:34.208 --> 44:36.333
[both chuckle]

44:37.000 --> 44:40.791
But you're so smart
and you're really good-looking.

44:40.875 --> 44:42.250
-[clears throat]
-Well, if I…

44:43.041 --> 44:44.125
[clears throat] Thank you.

44:45.375 --> 44:47.791
It's just, I look at people like you,

44:48.500 --> 44:52.333
and I just think how lucky you are
to be surrounded by your people.

44:52.416 --> 44:54.291
My wh-- My people? [chuckles]

44:54.375 --> 44:57.250
I wasn't born on Broadway. You know?

44:58.333 --> 45:00.625
I'm from Zelienople, Pennsylvania.

45:01.333 --> 45:03.333
Yeah, I grew up dirt poor.

45:04.041 --> 45:04.875
[clears throat]

45:05.750 --> 45:08.333
This whole… [rolls tongue]

45:09.041 --> 45:11.583
All this, I invented it.

45:12.166 --> 45:15.291
Yeah. I'm just a small-town girl and…

45:17.125 --> 45:19.000
-I had a big dream.
-Hmm.

45:22.500 --> 45:25.041
Single, just putting it out there.

45:25.125 --> 45:26.458
[both chuckle]

45:28.125 --> 45:30.333
Well, I'm divorced.

45:30.416 --> 45:33.208
Oh, I think I read about that.
Eddie Sharpe, the talk show host?

45:33.291 --> 45:34.958
Yeah, right.

45:35.041 --> 45:39.125
It lasted 15 heart-pulverizing years.

45:42.291 --> 45:46.375
I imagine it must be hard being
Dee Dee Allen, being a Broadway star.

45:46.458 --> 45:49.041
You know, it is hard.

45:50.625 --> 45:53.000
Sometimes I think I really…
I just want to quit.

45:53.083 --> 45:56.666
No. No, please, you can't--
You can't do that.

45:56.750 --> 45:58.208
[laughing] Why not?

45:58.791 --> 46:00.958
Because I need you to do what you do.

46:04.208 --> 46:06.375
♪ My days have little glamour ♪

46:06.458 --> 46:08.833
♪ Writing memos, making calls ♪

46:08.916 --> 46:13.125
♪ And wincing at the grammar
Written on the bathroom walls ♪

46:13.208 --> 46:16.500
♪ It's all school supplies
And budget size ♪

46:16.583 --> 46:19.000
♪ And wading through red tape ♪

46:20.250 --> 46:23.833
♪ That's why I love the theater ♪

46:23.916 --> 46:28.875
♪ It's how I escape ♪

46:30.083 --> 46:33.208
So, theater's a distraction.
Is that what you mean?

46:33.291 --> 46:37.083
A distraction is momentary.
An escape helps you heal.

46:37.166 --> 46:40.333
♪ We look to you ♪

46:40.416 --> 46:42.833
♪ To take us away ♪

46:42.916 --> 46:45.416
♪ From the soul-crushing jobs ♪

46:45.500 --> 46:47.791
♪ And emasculating pay ♪

46:47.875 --> 46:50.333
♪ When our lives come up short ♪

46:50.416 --> 46:53.291
♪ And our hopes are sad and few ♪

46:53.375 --> 46:58.250
♪ You whisk us off
To someplace strange and new ♪

47:01.125 --> 47:03.666
♪ We look to you ♪

47:03.750 --> 47:06.083
♪ In good times and bad ♪

47:06.166 --> 47:11.666
♪ The worlds you create
Make the real one seem less sad ♪

47:11.750 --> 47:14.416
♪ The curtain goes up ♪

47:14.500 --> 47:16.625
♪ And every now and then ♪

47:16.708 --> 47:22.666
♪ It feels as if we're coming home again ♪

47:22.750 --> 47:27.958
♪ Yes, coming home again ♪

47:29.375 --> 47:31.583
♪ We need a place to run to ♪

47:31.666 --> 47:34.083
♪ When everything goes wrong ♪

47:34.166 --> 47:38.375
♪ Where the answer to each problem
Is to burst into a song ♪

47:38.458 --> 47:40.875
♪ And standard rules of logic ♪

47:40.958 --> 47:43.875
♪ Just simply don't apply ♪

47:43.958 --> 47:46.833
♪ When people dance in unison ♪

47:46.916 --> 47:52.500
♪ And no one wonders why ♪

47:54.291 --> 47:57.583
[chuckles softly]
You make it sound so beautiful.

47:58.625 --> 48:01.000
♪ We look to you ♪

48:01.083 --> 48:03.958
♪ As strange as it seems ♪

48:04.041 --> 48:06.250
♪ When reality goes ♪

48:06.333 --> 48:09.250
♪ To scary new extremes ♪

48:09.333 --> 48:12.333
♪ So don't ever give up ♪

48:12.416 --> 48:16.208
♪ And this I guarantee ♪

48:17.166 --> 48:22.500
♪ Next time you think no one cares ♪

48:22.583 --> 48:27.958
♪ You can look ♪

48:28.041 --> 48:34.208
♪ To me ♪

48:34.291 --> 48:35.583
[audience cheering]

48:49.708 --> 48:52.625
-That's a nice picture.
-Oh, it's terrible.

48:53.166 --> 48:57.000
Look at the backdrop.
Clouds? What, are we flying?

48:57.083 --> 48:58.166
It's sweet.

48:58.916 --> 49:00.000
Well…

49:00.875 --> 49:04.250
you know, she needed proof
she was still part of the family,

49:04.333 --> 49:07.750
and nothing says family
like a Sears family portrait.

49:08.583 --> 49:11.458
-Is there booze in this?
-There sure is.

49:11.541 --> 49:14.500
-[coughs] When you said lemonade…
-Well, it's Indiana lemonade.

49:14.583 --> 49:18.541
Okay, it's official. I love you.
You're the cool grandmother I never had.

49:19.375 --> 49:23.041
Hey, let me ask you something.
What happened with Emma?

49:24.166 --> 49:25.250
[sighs]

49:25.750 --> 49:27.833
You're not a mother,
so you can't know what it's like

49:27.916 --> 49:30.375
to see your own daughter
give up her child.

49:30.458 --> 49:31.791
I'm sorry.

49:31.875 --> 49:36.000
When Emma came out,
oh, they could not handle it.

49:39.041 --> 49:41.625
To bad parents and their broken progeny.

49:42.875 --> 49:45.708
Although Emma is fine. She's a strong kid.

49:45.791 --> 49:46.625
[Barry] Mmm.

49:47.208 --> 49:48.958
Oh, I wasn't talking about her.

49:50.625 --> 49:52.875
What? You got kicked out too?

49:53.708 --> 49:56.125
Well, I left before they could do that.

49:59.166 --> 50:02.708
[Emma] So the only
nice dress I have is this.

50:02.791 --> 50:03.666
Wow.

50:04.666 --> 50:08.375
Okay, I mean, yeah, yep,
you could wear that to prom

50:08.458 --> 50:09.583
or keep it lying around

50:09.666 --> 50:12.083
in case there's a remake of
Little House on the Prairie.

50:12.166 --> 50:14.875
Okay. That's it. I like him.

50:14.958 --> 50:17.458
Emma, please let me
dress you for this prom.

50:17.541 --> 50:22.500
I don't know. This is all so crazy.
What did you wear to your prom?

50:22.583 --> 50:25.916
Well, I was going to wear a silver tux,

50:26.541 --> 50:29.333
aqua accessories, the whole look.

50:29.416 --> 50:32.500
I waited outside, anxious to see my crush,

50:32.583 --> 50:35.333
but when I saw him with his date, I froze.

50:36.083 --> 50:37.416
I couldn't go in.

50:38.291 --> 50:40.291
I didn't have your courage.

50:41.291 --> 50:42.666
This isn't about me.

50:43.708 --> 50:45.041
This is about you.

50:45.125 --> 50:48.625
And I promise you are going
to have the night of your life.

50:49.166 --> 50:50.500
What is your date wearing?

50:51.750 --> 50:52.750
I don't know.

50:54.333 --> 50:56.583
I've never been to her house before.

50:57.291 --> 50:58.916
Her mom doesn't know about us.

50:59.625 --> 51:01.083
How long have you been together?

51:01.916 --> 51:03.541
-A year and a half.
-Oh, honey.

51:03.625 --> 51:07.250
But she's coming out tonight, big time.
That's the plan.

51:09.208 --> 51:10.583
I'm really scared.

51:11.750 --> 51:13.166
Would you get over here?

51:13.916 --> 51:17.708
The point is you are brave.

51:17.791 --> 51:19.875
You made all this happen.

51:19.958 --> 51:23.041
When you walk into that gym tonight,
you know what people are gonna see?

51:23.125 --> 51:25.875
They're going to see
the bravest person on the planet.

51:25.958 --> 51:29.625
This is so hard.
Does every girl go through this?

51:29.708 --> 51:31.625
Yes, all across town,

51:31.708 --> 51:35.125
girls are spraying on their tans
and whitening their teeth,

51:35.208 --> 51:38.791
trying to look their best for the prom,
but they're wasting their time

51:38.875 --> 51:42.500
because they don't have the glow
that you have right now.

51:43.916 --> 51:47.375
I trust you completely,
and that's kind of scary too.

51:47.458 --> 51:50.041
Can we please go shop? Can we mall it?

51:50.791 --> 51:53.708
-Is that okay?
-Yes, mall the hell out of it!

51:53.791 --> 51:55.333
-Let's go.
-Okay!

51:55.416 --> 51:57.708
But get changed. This is disgusting.

