♪ Make it clear that tonight belongs ♪

57:22.666 --> 57:25.333
[Barry] Wait there.
I'll get the door. Okay? Okay.

57:25.416 --> 57:26.666
[Dee Dee squeals]

57:26.750 --> 57:28.958
-Are you ready?
-We're ready. We can't wait.

57:29.041 --> 57:32.166
-Here, hold this. I wanna get the picture.
-Okay. here we go.

57:32.250 --> 57:34.166
-[Sheldon] Wow.
-[Dee Dee] Oh, my God!

57:34.250 --> 57:36.833
-[gasps] Look at you!
-[Dee Dee squeals]

57:36.916 --> 57:38.208
You look amazing!

57:38.291 --> 57:40.291
[Emma] Are you sure it's not too girly?

57:40.375 --> 57:44.625
Aw. No, it's just
the right amount of girly.

57:45.416 --> 57:47.041
-You did well.
-Right?

57:47.541 --> 57:48.625
Hey, where's your date?

57:48.708 --> 57:52.166
We're meeting in the gym.
She's still a little shy about all this.

57:53.291 --> 57:55.791
Well, this is where we leave you.

57:55.875 --> 57:57.833
-[Angie laughs]
-Our work here is done.

57:58.958 --> 58:01.541
You go. You have the time of your life.

58:01.625 --> 58:04.208
Can you walk me in? I'm a little nervous.

58:04.958 --> 58:08.041
Of course. Hey, hold on tight.

58:08.125 --> 58:09.083
-Ready?
-Yep.

58:09.166 --> 58:11.166
-Clutch in this hand.
-Oh, sorry!

58:11.250 --> 58:12.083
Aw.

58:12.625 --> 58:13.625
Come on.

58:13.708 --> 58:15.916
-[Trent] Who wants punch?
-[Angie] Only if it's spiked.

58:16.000 --> 58:19.500
The walk away. The cute little truck.

58:20.083 --> 58:21.375
[camera shutter clicking]

58:29.458 --> 58:31.166
-[Emma] We're doin' it!
-[Barry] Go ahead.

58:39.083 --> 58:40.208
[Emma] What's going on?

58:40.291 --> 58:42.125
I'm putting the pieces together.
Gimme a sec.

58:42.208 --> 58:45.083
-[Barry] What is happening?
-[Emma] Where is everybody?

58:45.166 --> 58:49.833
Something is really wrong.
The whole parking lot is completely empty.

58:49.916 --> 58:52.708
[Sheldon] God. What's the theme
of this prom? Death row?

58:52.791 --> 58:55.833
Mr. Hawkins, where are all the kids?
I don't understand.

58:56.416 --> 58:58.500
Mom, what's happening?
Why aren't we at the gym?

58:58.583 --> 59:02.416
At the last minute, there was a problem,
so we had to change venues.

59:02.500 --> 59:04.375
No, Mom, what's going on?

59:04.458 --> 59:07.083
The courts told the PTA
they had to hold an inclusive prom.

59:07.166 --> 59:11.041
Don't worry. It's fine.
We did what we were required to do.

59:11.125 --> 59:12.500
There was some resistance.

59:12.583 --> 59:17.583
So the parents met without my knowledge,
and they've organized two proms.

59:17.666 --> 59:20.333
One for the kids
at the Elks Lodge in town.

59:20.416 --> 59:22.750
And this one just for you.

59:22.833 --> 59:25.541
-We gave her a prom.
-You did what?

59:25.625 --> 59:27.416
Wait, no, no.

59:27.500 --> 59:31.083
I got texts from kids at school.
Everybody said it was here.

59:31.166 --> 59:34.375
And they were lying to you.
It was part of the plan.

59:34.458 --> 59:36.666
-You lied to me.
-Oh, yeah? Who's the liar?

59:36.750 --> 59:40.125
We know about you and Emma,
and trust me, we're doing you a favor.

59:42.625 --> 59:43.458
No.

59:43.541 --> 59:47.333
-Oh, my God. This is so cruel.
-I'm gonna cry.

59:47.416 --> 59:50.125
Okay, honey. Look at me.

59:50.208 --> 59:51.291
-Angie.
-Yeah.

59:51.375 --> 59:53.375
-I want to go home.
-I know you do.

59:53.458 --> 59:57.083
-This isn't happening.
-And you got us, and this is awful.

59:57.166 --> 59:59.125
-No, no.
-Honey.

1:00:02.916 --> 1:00:06.166
♪ One thing's universal ♪

1:00:07.541 --> 1:00:10.791
♪ Life's no dress rehearsal ♪

1:00:11.833 --> 1:00:18.250
♪ When people find
A scapegoat to condemn ♪

1:00:20.333 --> 1:00:24.625
♪ We went big, yet we've blown it ♪

1:00:25.208 --> 1:00:29.458
♪ Well, I guess I should have known it ♪

1:00:30.125 --> 1:00:32.833
♪ All along tonight ♪

1:00:32.916 --> 1:00:36.083
♪ Belonged ♪

1:00:36.166 --> 1:00:39.791
♪ To them ♪

1:00:46.916 --> 1:00:48.625
[cell phone vibrating]

1:00:50.041 --> 1:00:52.458
-Alyssa?
-I swear I had no idea.

1:00:52.541 --> 1:00:55.250
How could you not know?
You were on the prom committee.

1:00:55.333 --> 1:00:57.125
It was Shelby and Kaylee.

1:00:57.208 --> 1:01:01.041
They figured out we were together
and they made sure I didn't find out.

1:01:01.125 --> 1:01:03.625
-They didn't want me to tell you.
-Then come meet me.

1:01:04.625 --> 1:01:05.583
I can't.

1:01:05.666 --> 1:01:07.458
Look, my mother's here.

1:01:07.541 --> 1:01:11.000
[crying] Well, leave her.
Tell her you're gay!

1:01:11.083 --> 1:01:13.958
Tell her we're in love.
That was the plan, wasn't it?

1:01:14.791 --> 1:01:16.125
[shakily] I'm really sorry.

1:01:17.833 --> 1:01:20.250
Have fun at the normal person's prom.

1:01:20.333 --> 1:01:21.916
-Wait. Emma.
-[call ends]

1:01:22.583 --> 1:01:23.458
Emma!

1:01:23.541 --> 1:01:24.375
[sniffles]

1:01:27.583 --> 1:01:31.833
Okay. Here's what we're gonna do.
We are going to that prom, okay?

1:01:31.916 --> 1:01:34.541
They can't stop us.
We will march into that room--

1:01:34.625 --> 1:01:37.625
No! No, enough.

1:01:38.458 --> 1:01:40.791
This is already
the worst night of my life.

1:01:40.875 --> 1:01:43.666
Please, just stop helping me.

1:01:48.625 --> 1:01:50.458
Emma! Emma!

1:01:52.208 --> 1:01:55.625
This is a complete disaster.

1:01:55.708 --> 1:01:57.500
[Sheldon] This is a PR problem.

1:01:57.583 --> 1:02:02.541
No, Sheldon.
We had a PR problem back in New York.

1:02:03.250 --> 1:02:05.208
This was supposed to solve that.

1:02:06.208 --> 1:02:07.250
But this…

1:02:08.166 --> 1:02:10.541
This is heartbreaking.

1:02:10.625 --> 1:02:14.833
This is why you came here? For publicity?

1:02:23.916 --> 1:02:25.083
[sniffles]

1:02:31.750 --> 1:02:32.833
[indistinct chatter]

1:02:32.916 --> 1:02:35.375
[Mrs. Greene] I have been asked
to read a statement.

1:02:35.458 --> 1:02:40.125
"What happened here
was not the result of some elaborate plan

1:02:40.208 --> 1:02:44.708
to humiliate this girl,
as has been reported in the press."

1:02:44.791 --> 1:02:48.375
"The James Madison High School
Parent-Teacher Association

1:02:48.458 --> 1:02:51.333
felt Emma would not be safe

1:02:51.416 --> 1:02:54.750
if we allowed her
to attend prom with the other students

1:02:54.833 --> 1:02:57.166
because the uncomfortable truth

1:02:57.250 --> 1:03:03.041
is there are people in our community
who are offended by her life choices."

1:03:04.166 --> 1:03:08.083
I can't even wrap my head around this.
It's a nightmare. Oh, my God!

1:03:09.416 --> 1:03:11.750
I wanna be the cockeyed optimist here

1:03:11.833 --> 1:03:14.166
'cause I played Nellie Forbush
in South Pacific.

1:03:14.250 --> 1:03:16.458
It was a dinner theater production, but…

1:03:16.541 --> 1:03:17.375
Ugh.

1:03:19.041 --> 1:03:21.416
This is horrible. It really is.

1:03:22.000 --> 1:03:24.916
Thanks for hanging out with me
these past couple of days.

1:03:25.000 --> 1:03:26.375
You've been a good friend.

1:03:27.041 --> 1:03:31.291
-I have?
-You have. You seem surprised.

1:03:31.375 --> 1:03:33.000
No, I just…

1:03:34.458 --> 1:03:37.375
I'm a chorus girl. You know, I just…

1:03:38.208 --> 1:03:39.041
[sighs]

1:03:39.708 --> 1:03:43.041
No one ever thanks me.
They don't even see me.

1:03:45.166 --> 1:03:47.875
Spend my whole life
trying to stay in the game,

1:03:49.541 --> 1:03:51.375
and keep my day-drinking under control.

1:03:51.458 --> 1:03:52.291
[snickers]

1:03:52.958 --> 1:03:55.166
That's really nice. Thanks, kid.

1:03:57.583 --> 1:04:01.375
Hey, you're going to get through this.
I know it.

1:04:02.166 --> 1:04:03.333
[inhales shakily]

1:04:04.250 --> 1:04:08.125
I thought that when my parents
rejected me and stopped loving me

1:04:08.208 --> 1:04:10.291
that I would never feel any worse,
you know?

1:04:10.875 --> 1:04:11.833
Mmm-hmm.

1:04:11.916 --> 1:04:13.416
And now this…

1:04:15.250 --> 1:04:16.458
And I feel worse.

1:04:16.541 --> 1:04:19.875
-Honey…
-I've never felt so alone in my life.

1:04:19.958 --> 1:04:23.208
But you're not alone. You're not.

1:04:23.291 --> 1:04:25.041
You got me. Hmm?

1:04:25.625 --> 1:04:29.666
And we are ride-or-die,
and you do have friends.

1:04:30.666 --> 1:04:31.708
Where are they?

1:04:37.708 --> 1:04:39.291
-[Dee Dee] This is it.
-[Trent] Yes.

1:04:39.375 --> 1:04:40.750
-No.
-Well, okay.

1:04:43.791 --> 1:04:44.916
[knocking on door]

1:04:45.875 --> 1:04:47.875
-[doorbell rings]
-[knocking at door]

1:04:47.958 --> 1:04:50.125
-Emma, can we come in?
-Yes.

1:04:50.208 --> 1:04:52.708
-We brought Häagen-Dazs.
-[Trent] That's fancy ice cream.

1:04:52.791 --> 1:04:55.666
I know what Häagen-Dazs is. Hand it over.

1:04:55.750 --> 1:04:58.500
Emma, I know you said
you didn't want us to help anymore,

1:04:58.583 --> 1:05:02.291
but we cannot let them get away with this.
We have got to fight back.

1:05:02.375 --> 1:05:04.583
Okay, I know everybody's really angry.

1:05:05.625 --> 1:05:09.083
But I think we have to admit
that we have made things worse.

1:05:09.166 --> 1:05:13.666
I think the best thing we can do
is disinfect our things and go back home.

1:05:13.750 --> 1:05:15.500
-No, we are not leaving.
-No!

1:05:15.583 --> 1:05:19.958
Dee Dee, we are gonna stay here,
and we're going to turn this thing around.

1:05:20.041 --> 1:05:22.250
-We gotta take back the press.
-[Trent] Yes, how?

1:05:22.333 --> 1:05:26.000
Emma, you've got to step up
and be the face of this thing.

1:05:26.083 --> 1:05:27.750
And that's going to get her a prom?

1:05:27.833 --> 1:05:31.541
This is not about a prom anymore.
This is about right and wrong.

1:05:31.625 --> 1:05:34.375
We need a national audience, prime time.

1:05:34.458 --> 1:05:37.500
You want a big audience fast?
We gotta use our ace in the hole.

1:05:38.875 --> 1:05:41.125
-One call to Eddie Sharpe is all we need.
-No. No.

1:05:41.208 --> 1:05:42.416
-[Trent] Dee Dee!
-He's right.

1:05:42.500 --> 1:05:45.541
If I ask him for something,
he will want something in return,

1:05:45.625 --> 1:05:47.375
and what he will want
is the Hamptons house.

1:05:47.458 --> 1:05:48.958
He's been trying to get it for years.

1:05:49.833 --> 1:05:53.541
Okay. Okay, fine. Look, Sheldon,
you got to get that girl on TV.

1:05:53.625 --> 1:05:55.000
-Okay.
-Great.

1:05:55.083 --> 1:05:57.000
No, not great.

1:05:57.083 --> 1:06:00.333
I'm sorry, but there is no way
I'm getting in front of a camera

1:06:00.416 --> 1:06:03.375
and telling my story
to millions of people. I can't do that.

1:06:03.458 --> 1:06:07.500
-See?
-Please. Please, just go.

1:06:08.458 --> 1:06:11.875
-Emma, if you do nothing-- Okay.
-Barry. Go.

1:06:13.541 --> 1:06:17.166
-Okay, I get it. Okay. Okay.
-[Angie] Go. Go, go, go. Go, go.

1:06:17.250 --> 1:06:19.291
[whispering] I got this.
I know what I'm doing.

1:06:20.833 --> 1:06:22.041
Let me do my thing.

1:06:24.041 --> 1:06:26.958
There must be a way to rid this community,
and by extension, the nation,

1:06:27.041 --> 1:06:28.500
of this cancer of intolerance.

1:06:28.583 --> 1:06:30.875
What are you even doing here?
What happened to Godspell?

1:06:30.958 --> 1:06:34.333
Indianapolis was canceled,
as was the naval base at Guantánamo Bay.

1:06:34.416 --> 1:06:36.208
What I'm thinking I'm going to do is this.

1:06:36.291 --> 1:06:39.541
Venture forth and seek out
the young people and rap,

1:06:39.625 --> 1:06:41.041
in a non-musical sense.

1:06:49.583 --> 1:06:50.416
[Angie] Mmm.

1:06:55.250 --> 1:06:56.750
Let's go get some more, huh?

1:06:57.583 --> 1:06:58.833
Two spoons this time.

1:06:59.916 --> 1:07:00.916
Come on.

1:07:04.250 --> 1:07:06.166
[Angie] Gotta stop. [chuckling]

1:07:06.250 --> 1:07:11.791
Before you lecture me or kick me to death
with those crazy antelope legs of yours,

1:07:11.875 --> 1:07:15.583
or whatever you're gonna do,
I know I should do something.

1:07:16.958 --> 1:07:18.500
I just can't.

1:07:18.583 --> 1:07:20.125
You gotta do this.

1:07:20.208 --> 1:07:22.083
You gotta do it for all of us people

1:07:22.166 --> 1:07:25.791
that are standing in the wings,
waiting to go on.

1:07:27.083 --> 1:07:29.500
-I'm too scared.
-Hmm.

1:07:31.666 --> 1:07:33.083
Let me tell you a story.

1:07:34.083 --> 1:07:36.750
It's 1975

1:07:36.833 --> 1:07:40.041
and the original company of Chicago
is in previews,

1:07:40.125 --> 1:07:43.041
and the worst flu in history
hits the cast.

1:07:43.125 --> 1:07:47.291
They're down to the third cover
for the role of Roxie Hart

1:07:47.375 --> 1:07:50.291
and she's scared, just like you are.

1:07:50.375 --> 1:07:56.666
And Fosse, who is a real ballbuster,
is putting her through her paces

1:07:56.750 --> 1:07:58.458
and she's petrified.

1:07:58.541 --> 1:08:01.166
Worst of all, she's doing the routine
like she's a robot.

1:08:01.250 --> 1:08:07.625
So the Foss, he says,
"Hey, kid. Snap out of it."

1:08:08.125 --> 1:08:09.583
[jazz music playing]

1:08:09.666 --> 1:08:11.875
"You got the steps."

1:08:11.958 --> 1:08:14.250
"You've got the notes."

1:08:15.416 --> 1:08:18.833
"Where's the zazz, baby?"

1:08:20.208 --> 1:08:23.666
And even though
she'd never heard that word before,

1:08:23.750 --> 1:08:26.041
she knew immediately what it meant.

1:08:26.125 --> 1:08:29.375
And she went out there
and she found that spotlight,

1:08:29.458 --> 1:08:32.250
and she crushed that performance so hard,

1:08:32.333 --> 1:08:39.125
she had that whole audience standing
on their feet screaming bloody murder!

1:08:39.208 --> 1:08:40.041
[sighs]

1:08:40.791 --> 1:08:42.250
And that girl was you!

1:08:43.125 --> 1:08:44.125
What?

1:08:44.875 --> 1:08:46.375
How old do you think I am?

1:08:46.458 --> 1:08:50.666
It was 1975! No.

1:08:50.750 --> 1:08:56.541
The point is
every Fosse girl knows that story.

1:08:56.625 --> 1:09:00.625
It's all about finding your light.

1:09:02.333 --> 1:09:07.416
♪ When a challenge lies ahead
And you are filled with dread and worry ♪

1:09:08.333 --> 1:09:09.750
♪ Give it some zazz ♪

1:09:09.833 --> 1:09:15.833
♪ If your courage disappears
What'll get your fears to scurry? ♪

1:09:16.458 --> 1:09:17.541
♪ Give it some zazz ♪

1:09:17.625 --> 1:09:21.916
♪ Zazz is style plus confidence ♪

1:09:22.000 --> 1:09:25.916
♪ It may seem corny or kitsch ♪

1:09:26.000 --> 1:09:29.458
♪ But when scared or on the fence ♪

1:09:29.541 --> 1:09:33.000
♪ You'll find that zazz
Will soon make fear become your bitch ♪

1:09:34.375 --> 1:09:39.833
♪ And if folks say you can't win
What'll stop them in a hurry? ♪

1:09:40.666 --> 1:09:41.958
♪ Give it some zazz ♪

1:09:42.541 --> 1:09:49.416
♪ There's no contest for a girl
Who has some razzmatazz ♪

1:09:50.083 --> 1:09:53.833
♪ So call their bluff
And strut your stuff ♪

1:09:53.916 --> 1:09:57.666
♪ Like no chick in this hick town has ♪

1:09:57.750 --> 1:10:00.791
♪ Instead of giving up ♪

1:10:03.458 --> 1:10:05.333
♪ Oh, give it some zazz ♪

1:10:05.416 --> 1:10:07.208
I just don't think I can do it.

1:10:07.291 --> 1:10:10.208
The thought of getting up
in front of all of those people.

1:10:10.291 --> 1:10:12.041
Look at my hands, they're shaking.

1:10:12.875 --> 1:10:14.500
♪ If your hands are shakin' ♪

1:10:14.583 --> 1:10:20.291
♪ Just turn 'em into jazz hands ♪

1:10:20.375 --> 1:10:22.416
-Doesn't that feel better?
-No.

1:10:22.500 --> 1:10:23.833
Try this.

1:10:28.750 --> 1:10:29.916
This is awkward.

1:10:30.000 --> 1:10:32.666
You don't understand the concept of zazz.

1:10:32.750 --> 1:10:37.583
The zazz is not the moves.
The zazz comes from within.

1:10:37.666 --> 1:10:41.708
Do the moves and give it some zazz.

1:10:42.333 --> 1:10:43.500
Close your eyes.

1:10:44.458 --> 1:10:45.625
Think about Mrs. Greene.

1:10:46.666 --> 1:10:48.541
Think about that fake prom.

1:10:49.833 --> 1:10:53.708
Now think of finally
doing something about it.

1:10:55.000 --> 1:10:59.833
-Oh, I'm seeing it! I'm seeing your zazz!
-[chuckling]

1:11:00.416 --> 1:11:02.083
Now, follow me!

1:11:02.958 --> 1:11:06.875
♪ Do like the brave and bossy do ♪

1:11:06.958 --> 1:11:09.791
♪ And if they tear you apart ♪

1:11:10.833 --> 1:11:13.916
♪ Ask what would Bob Fosse do? ♪

1:11:14.500 --> 1:11:17.625
♪ He'd make the people
Have a step-ball-change of heart ♪

1:11:17.708 --> 1:11:19.166
♪ Ball change! ♪

1:11:19.250 --> 1:11:24.333
♪ And if folks say you can't win
What'll stop them in a hurry? ♪

1:11:25.250 --> 1:11:27.000
♪ Give it some zazz ♪

1:11:27.083 --> 1:11:33.500
♪ There's no contest for a girl
Who has some razzmatazz ♪

1:11:34.666 --> 1:11:36.500
♪ So call their bluff, bam! ♪

1:11:36.583 --> 1:11:38.541
♪ And strut my stuff, bam! ♪

1:11:38.625 --> 1:11:42.166
♪ Like no chick
In this hick town has ♪

1:11:42.250 --> 1:11:45.166
♪ Instead of giving up ♪

1:11:48.166 --> 1:11:50.041
♪ Give it some zazz ♪

1:11:51.083 --> 1:11:55.333
Now that you found your zazz,
it's time to show it to the world.

1:11:55.416 --> 1:11:57.833
-You think you know how?
-Yeah!

1:11:57.916 --> 1:11:59.833
[both laughing]

1:12:01.333 --> 1:12:05.625
You've sort of been,
you know, the woman in my life.

1:12:08.958 --> 1:12:10.375
You've been the man in mine.

1:12:12.125 --> 1:12:14.541
[man] And I was thinking
this could be our last time…

1:12:14.625 --> 1:12:15.958
We shouldn't be doing this.

1:12:16.041 --> 1:12:20.458
Oh, it's rom-com Friday.
Rom-com Friday is sacred.

1:12:20.541 --> 1:12:21.791
We should be helping Emma.

1:12:21.875 --> 1:12:25.458
-We gotta get her on TV.
-Sheldon is on it. Come on.

1:12:26.750 --> 1:12:29.458
-How does this work, anyway?
-[Barry] It's infrared.

1:12:29.541 --> 1:12:32.333
-It reduces inflammation.
-[Dee Dee] Oh, good.

1:12:32.416 --> 1:12:34.791
But you can't keep it on too long.
It'll blow your face off.

1:12:35.458 --> 1:12:36.416
What?

1:12:36.500 --> 1:12:38.166
[both chuckling]

1:12:40.750 --> 1:12:44.708
♪ Someday when I'm awfully low ♪

1:12:45.666 --> 1:12:47.875
♪ And the world is cold… ♪

1:12:47.958 --> 1:12:49.541
Saw this movie with Eddie.

1:12:52.625 --> 1:12:54.541
-It was our first date.
-[Barry] Was it really?

1:12:54.625 --> 1:12:56.083
-Yeah.
-[Barry] Mmm.

1:12:57.666 --> 1:13:01.416
Then he… took me out for dinner after.

1:13:02.041 --> 1:13:04.875
Well, I took him out. [chuckles]

1:13:04.958 --> 1:13:06.250
He didn't have any money.

1:13:06.333 --> 1:13:11.416
He was just starting out in comedy,
and he didn't have the big show like now.

1:13:13.208 --> 1:13:15.291
Fifteen years, he didn't have any money.

1:13:16.250 --> 1:13:18.750
And I picked up the tab. I paid.

1:13:20.666 --> 1:13:23.625
-[Barry] That was a bad move.
-[Dee Dee] No kidding. I'm still paying.

1:13:25.250 --> 1:13:27.250
[Dee Dee sighs]

1:13:29.500 --> 1:13:31.125
Can I make an observation?

1:13:31.208 --> 1:13:36.333
[sighs] Is it a pleasant observation
or is it an irritating one?

1:13:36.416 --> 1:13:37.625
You're not over him.

1:13:37.708 --> 1:13:39.500
No, don't say that. I am not…

1:13:39.583 --> 1:13:41.750
Trust me. I am…

1:13:41.833 --> 1:13:44.041
[chuckling] I am way over him.

1:13:44.125 --> 1:13:47.875
I'm just mad at myself, you know, I am so…

1:13:48.583 --> 1:13:50.666
Why it took me so long to…

1:13:51.958 --> 1:13:53.166
figure it out.

1:13:53.958 --> 1:13:58.000
You know? I believed him.
I believed him every single time.

1:13:59.000 --> 1:14:01.083
"I promise you, it's nothing."

1:14:01.166 --> 1:14:03.916
"It's meaningless.
She's nothing to me. It's over."

1:14:05.333 --> 1:14:08.541
I finally got the message, you know.
He didn't love me. [chuckles]

1:14:10.750 --> 1:14:11.750
He didn't…

1:14:12.666 --> 1:14:14.791
[chuckling] He didn't even like me.

1:14:16.666 --> 1:14:18.041
But he liked the money.

1:14:18.833 --> 1:14:21.625
Oh, yeah, so I got out.

1:14:23.375 --> 1:14:24.375
I got out…

1:14:25.541 --> 1:14:27.416
and I gave him half my money.

1:14:28.750 --> 1:14:31.916
And now here we are, singing to trucks.

1:14:32.000 --> 1:14:34.000
-And he's got a hit TV show.
-[audience cheering]

1:14:34.083 --> 1:14:36.708
And I still owe him
half my unemployment check.

1:14:36.791 --> 1:14:38.791
[announcer on TV] It's Eddie Sharpe!

1:14:38.875 --> 1:14:40.125
[Eddie] Whoa, hey!

1:14:40.208 --> 1:14:43.291
Welcome, everybody!
What's today's words of wisdom?

1:14:43.375 --> 1:14:45.875
[Eddie and audience] Never sign a prenup!

1:14:45.958 --> 1:14:47.666
[all laughing through TV]

1:14:50.708 --> 1:14:53.291
And you know what the worst part is?

1:14:55.083 --> 1:14:56.000
I shut down.

1:14:58.208 --> 1:15:03.250
He took my little,
delicate blueberry heart,

1:15:03.333 --> 1:15:05.916
and he just… squished it.

1:15:07.666 --> 1:15:08.500
[Dee Dee sniffles]

1:15:10.541 --> 1:15:13.375
-What?
-Here's what you're gonna do, okay?

1:15:14.125 --> 1:15:18.041
You're gonna wear something
heart-stopping, like that yellow cape

1:15:18.125 --> 1:15:19.750
and those cute little boots.

1:15:19.833 --> 1:15:21.583
And you are gonna march down

1:15:21.666 --> 1:15:25.583
to that principal's office
like a bad, bad girl.

1:15:25.666 --> 1:15:27.333
[chuckling] Tom?

1:15:27.416 --> 1:15:29.791
-Tom is a fan. Friend.
-[Barry] Hmm?

1:15:29.875 --> 1:15:31.041
Well…

1:15:32.250 --> 1:15:33.375
he likes you.

1:15:34.541 --> 1:15:36.250
As a fan. Friend.

1:15:37.541 --> 1:15:40.083
I don't know.
Not even that much anymore.

1:15:40.166 --> 1:15:42.583
Okay, let's cut the crap.
I would kill, kill,

1:15:42.666 --> 1:15:45.416
to have a guy look at me
the way that he looks at you.

1:15:45.500 --> 1:15:47.500
Stop it.

1:15:48.416 --> 1:15:52.666
You're just…
You're poking my heart with your finger.

1:15:53.375 --> 1:15:56.416
Your still-beating,
delicate little blueberry heart?

1:16:02.250 --> 1:16:05.916
Do you think he really, really likes me?

1:16:06.000 --> 1:16:07.083
Oh, my God, yes!

1:16:08.083 --> 1:16:09.416
Barry! [kisses]

1:16:09.500 --> 1:16:11.125
[laughing]

1:16:11.208 --> 1:16:14.166
-I love you! I love you!
-I love you! I love you!

1:16:14.250 --> 1:16:16.541
You're just such a great… everything.

1:16:16.625 --> 1:16:18.333
[laughing]

1:16:19.125 --> 1:16:21.083
[Dee Dee] Okay, no, no, no. Okay.

1:16:22.000 --> 1:16:24.083
This, the master stroke, your idea.

1:16:24.166 --> 1:16:26.625
-And the boots?
-And the little cute boots.

1:16:26.708 --> 1:16:27.666
[chuckling]

1:16:28.666 --> 1:16:29.833
This is it.

1:16:31.708 --> 1:16:32.708
Oh!

1:16:33.541 --> 1:16:35.458
That is good.

1:16:39.833 --> 1:16:41.875
Mmm, now…

1:16:42.833 --> 1:16:43.666
you.

1:16:46.458 --> 1:16:48.791
I've been thinking about you
since we got here.

1:16:48.875 --> 1:16:51.791
Oh, God. I knew this was gonna
somehow turn around to me.

1:16:51.875 --> 1:16:57.250
And I think it's time somebody poked
that gay little heart of yours.

1:16:57.333 --> 1:16:59.250
Are we doing this? Fine. Uh…

1:16:59.333 --> 1:17:02.666
Do I only go for 10s
when I know I'm a 6.2? Yes and--

1:17:02.750 --> 1:17:06.083
Your parents. You're from Ohio, right?

1:17:06.166 --> 1:17:07.416
So?

1:17:08.291 --> 1:17:09.666
We're in Indiana.

1:17:09.750 --> 1:17:13.500
-Ohio, Indiana, they're close.
-I can see where you're driving this.

1:17:13.583 --> 1:17:15.958
You have two living parents

1:17:16.041 --> 1:17:19.291
that you'll never be nearer to
than you are right now.

1:17:19.375 --> 1:17:22.166
-I think you should call them.
-No.

1:17:23.041 --> 1:17:24.416
They threw me away.

1:17:24.500 --> 1:17:26.750
Well, did they really?

1:17:26.833 --> 1:17:28.250
I told them that I was gay,

1:17:28.333 --> 1:17:32.166
and they said that they would take me
to therapy to change myself completely.

1:17:34.208 --> 1:17:37.875
Let your parents see who you are
before it's too late.

1:17:40.625 --> 1:17:41.708
If you don't…

1:17:42.750 --> 1:17:43.750
you'll regret it.

1:17:45.875 --> 1:17:48.250
I'm not the one who should have regrets.

1:17:50.291 --> 1:17:51.875
[voice breaking] I was the kid.

1:17:52.958 --> 1:17:54.208
I was the kid!

1:17:56.375 --> 1:17:57.958
[crying] I was 16.

1:18:00.500 --> 1:18:03.458
Sixteen years old. I was terrified.

1:18:03.541 --> 1:18:05.000
Terrified!

1:18:08.125 --> 1:18:11.166
And I needed one thing from them
and they couldn't give it to me.

1:18:11.250 --> 1:18:12.125
So don't you…

1:18:13.708 --> 1:18:14.791
[sobbing]

1:18:30.291 --> 1:18:31.875
[school bell ringing]

1:18:33.666 --> 1:18:35.458
[woman over PA]
Would the following students

1:18:35.541 --> 1:18:37.583
please report to after-school detention?

1:18:38.458 --> 1:18:39.416
Harlan Doolittle…

1:18:39.500 --> 1:18:40.333
Hi.

1:18:40.416 --> 1:18:42.875
…Olivia Blanc, Frances Doolittle.
Thank you.

1:18:43.958 --> 1:18:45.875
[Principal Hawkins]
Well, they each had a bite.

1:18:45.958 --> 1:18:48.791
-Ooh, what'd you do?
-[Principal Hawkins] Yeah, a big bite.

1:18:48.875 --> 1:18:50.875
I appreciate it. Bye-bye.

1:18:52.375 --> 1:18:53.583
[Dee Dee chuckles softly]

1:18:54.166 --> 1:18:56.083
Am I interrupting something?

1:18:56.166 --> 1:18:58.041
I was just doing some research,

1:18:58.125 --> 1:19:01.333
trying to figure out
if urinal cakes are poisonous.

1:19:02.000 --> 1:19:04.125
-Uh, how can I help you?
-[chuckles softly]

1:19:04.750 --> 1:19:09.750
Well, I've just been wandering
around town all day.

1:19:09.833 --> 1:19:11.250
[chuckles]

1:19:11.833 --> 1:19:15.125
I've seen the… sight. [chuckles softly]

1:19:15.708 --> 1:19:16.708
And, um…

1:19:18.458 --> 1:19:23.125
Bottom line is I just thought
you might want to take me to dinner

1:19:23.208 --> 1:19:26.041
and worship me again. [chuckles]

1:19:26.125 --> 1:19:27.750
No, I would not like to do that.

1:19:27.833 --> 1:19:30.291
Now if you'll excuse me,
I've got work to do.

1:19:30.375 --> 1:19:33.625
Okay, what's going on here?
Why is everybody always so mad at me?

1:19:33.708 --> 1:19:37.583
Well, speaking for myself,
it's because you're an opportunist.

1:19:37.666 --> 1:19:40.583
You came here for publicity.
You're a terrible person.

1:19:40.666 --> 1:19:43.041
No, no. Nobody gets to
talk to me that way. Nobody!

1:19:44.000 --> 1:19:47.000
You know, meeting you in person
has been colossally disappointing.

1:19:47.083 --> 1:19:48.208
[scoffs]

1:19:48.291 --> 1:19:50.083
I wanted you to be Dolores.

1:19:50.166 --> 1:19:51.833
Who the hell is Dolores?

1:19:51.916 --> 1:19:53.708
From Swallow the Moon.

1:19:53.791 --> 1:19:54.750
[audience applauding]

1:19:54.833 --> 1:19:58.541
[Principal Hawkins] She was joyful.
She was full of courage and hope.

1:19:58.625 --> 1:20:01.625
-Okay, but she was fictional.
-But you made her real.

1:20:03.250 --> 1:20:05.833
When you sang
"The Lady's Improving" to Troy Gibson,

1:20:05.916 --> 1:20:09.125
you were admitting you weren't perfect
and you knew you could be better,

1:20:09.208 --> 1:20:11.875
and that's why
he didn't fire you from the circus act.

1:20:13.333 --> 1:20:15.791
Such humility and dignity.

1:20:16.458 --> 1:20:18.916
-That's who I thought you were.
-Well, I'm not.

1:20:19.916 --> 1:20:21.541
I'm not Dolores.

1:20:23.166 --> 1:20:28.041
I'm just a really, really,
really good actress. And you…

1:20:28.666 --> 1:20:30.916
You're just some hick town
high school teacher

1:20:31.000 --> 1:20:34.541
who can't even tell the difference
between fantasy and reality.

1:20:34.625 --> 1:20:36.500
-Are we done?
-Oh, yeah, we're done.

1:20:42.708 --> 1:20:43.625
[sighs]

1:20:47.791 --> 1:20:52.583
♪ The lady's improving ♪

1:20:53.583 --> 1:20:57.000
♪ So don't give up hope ♪

1:21:00.458 --> 1:21:04.625
♪ You ask, "Is she perfect?" ♪

1:21:04.708 --> 1:21:09.166
♪ My answer is nope ♪

1:21:09.250 --> 1:21:11.625
-I know what you're doing.
-[chuckles]

1:21:12.750 --> 1:21:16.208
♪ Her range needs expanding ♪

1:21:16.291 --> 1:21:19.541
♪ Her edges need sanding ♪

1:21:19.625 --> 1:21:25.458
♪ But she can become a sure bet ♪

1:21:25.541 --> 1:21:27.333
♪ So I'm begging you, sir ♪

1:21:27.416 --> 1:21:30.791
♪ Don't give up on her yet ♪

1:21:30.875 --> 1:21:32.541
You're trying to appeal to the fan in me.

1:21:32.625 --> 1:21:34.125
It won't work. I'm not a fan anymore.

1:21:34.208 --> 1:21:39.250
♪ The lady's improving
So much that she gloats ♪

1:21:40.083 --> 1:21:42.583
♪ I know you've got standards ♪

1:21:42.666 --> 1:21:45.250
♪ Feel free to give notes ♪

1:21:45.333 --> 1:21:51.916
♪ There isn't an issue
And that's why I wish you could see ♪

1:21:52.000 --> 1:21:56.625
♪ There's no reason to fret ♪

1:21:56.708 --> 1:21:58.083
♪ So I'm begging you, sir ♪

1:21:58.166 --> 1:22:01.208
♪ Don't give up on her yet ♪

1:22:01.291 --> 1:22:03.791
Seriously, Dee Dee, this is unsettling.

1:22:03.875 --> 1:22:06.583
It's like having a fantasy
I don't want to have.

1:22:06.666 --> 1:22:11.875
♪ Everybody thinks that I've got
Some kinks that I'll never work out ♪

1:22:11.958 --> 1:22:17.625
♪ Even you're inclined
To think I'm unrefined ♪

1:22:17.708 --> 1:22:20.083
♪ But I promise with some time ♪

1:22:20.166 --> 1:22:23.083
♪ That my aptitude will climb ♪

1:22:23.166 --> 1:22:30.125
♪ And you'll leave your doubts
And disbeliefs behind ♪

1:22:31.708 --> 1:22:35.791
♪ The lady's improving
Removing all doubt ♪

1:22:35.875 --> 1:22:37.208
-[boy 1 whistles]
-Hey!

1:22:37.291 --> 1:22:42.666
