[chuckling] ♪ To the freakin' prom ♪

1:38:45.791 --> 1:38:46.916
[crowd cheering]

1:38:54.500 --> 1:38:55.958
Going to the prom.

1:39:01.750 --> 1:39:05.541
♪ In showbiz
I never felt such a thrill divine ♪

1:39:06.458 --> 1:39:10.791
♪ My date is a high school lesbian
Still it's fine ♪

1:39:10.875 --> 1:39:15.125
♪ And though it's been years
I might call my mom ♪

1:39:15.208 --> 1:39:20.250
♪ And tell her that though it's overdue
All of my waiting is over too ♪

1:39:20.333 --> 1:39:22.208
♪ And if you're not happy, I'm over you ♪

1:39:22.291 --> 1:39:25.541
♪ 'Cause Barry ♪

1:39:26.375 --> 1:39:29.541
♪ Yes, Barry ♪

1:39:29.625 --> 1:39:30.583
Go on.

1:39:30.666 --> 1:39:32.000
♪ Look at me, Mom ♪

1:39:32.083 --> 1:39:34.166
♪ Barry's going to… ♪

1:39:35.041 --> 1:39:41.041
♪ Prom ♪

1:39:41.125 --> 1:39:42.333
♪ Yeah! ♪

1:39:43.083 --> 1:39:44.083
[panting]

1:40:05.916 --> 1:40:07.041
Hello, interweb.

1:40:08.041 --> 1:40:11.583
My name is Emma Nolan,
and I'm 17 and I'm gay.

1:40:12.708 --> 1:40:15.500
You might have heard
about the fake prom in Indiana.

1:40:15.583 --> 1:40:16.750
That was me.

1:40:17.625 --> 1:40:20.041
It was awful in every way,

1:40:20.125 --> 1:40:23.541
and I spent a lot of time
feeling sorry for myself.

1:40:23.625 --> 1:40:26.791
So I wrote a song
for all the people out there

1:40:27.500 --> 1:40:32.333
who love someone in a way
that the world just doesn't understand.

1:40:32.416 --> 1:40:36.041
I know we all have stories to tell,
and here's mine.

1:40:38.125 --> 1:40:42.958
♪ Some hearts can conform
Fitting the norm ♪

1:40:43.041 --> 1:40:46.625
♪ Flaunting their love for all to see ♪

1:40:46.708 --> 1:40:53.250
♪ I tried to change
Thinking how easy life could be ♪

1:40:53.333 --> 1:40:56.083
♪ I just kept on failing ♪

1:40:56.166 --> 1:41:00.041
♪ I guess that was a sign ♪

1:41:00.708 --> 1:41:03.666
♪ That there wasn't much hope ♪

1:41:03.750 --> 1:41:08.041
♪ For this unruly heart ♪

1:41:08.125 --> 1:41:12.250
♪ Of mine ♪

1:41:12.333 --> 1:41:16.750
♪ Then you came along
And right or wrong ♪

1:41:16.833 --> 1:41:20.125
♪ Feelings began to overflow ♪

1:41:20.208 --> 1:41:26.541
♪ We had to hide
Thinking that no one else could know ♪

1:41:26.625 --> 1:41:33.041
♪ And not having you near me
Was where I drew the line ♪

1:41:33.125 --> 1:41:36.208
♪ So I had to conceal ♪

1:41:36.291 --> 1:41:41.791
♪ This poor unruly heart ♪

1:41:41.875 --> 1:41:45.666
♪ Of mine ♪

1:41:45.750 --> 1:41:49.375
Hi, Emma.
I loved your video. Where do I start?

1:41:49.458 --> 1:41:51.000
I think my parents always knew.

1:41:51.083 --> 1:41:54.708
I felt so alone.
Nothing made sense until him.

1:41:54.791 --> 1:41:56.333
She's the best thing in my life.

1:41:56.416 --> 1:41:58.500
The only good thing.

1:41:58.583 --> 1:41:59.833
But we're always hiding.

1:41:59.916 --> 1:42:01.791
[fan on laptop]
You're not the only one.

1:42:02.791 --> 1:42:05.458
♪ And though I don't know how or when ♪

1:42:05.541 --> 1:42:09.291
♪ But somehow I learned to see ♪

1:42:09.375 --> 1:42:12.666
[all] ♪ No matter what
The world might say ♪

1:42:12.750 --> 1:42:19.333
♪ This heart is the best part of me ♪

1:42:23.166 --> 1:42:27.625
♪ So fear's all in the past
Fading so fast ♪

1:42:27.708 --> 1:42:30.958
♪ I won't stay hidden anymore ♪

1:42:31.041 --> 1:42:32.750
♪ I'm who I am ♪

1:42:32.833 --> 1:42:36.583
♪ And I think that's worth fighting for ♪

1:42:36.666 --> 1:42:39.583
♪ And nobody out there ♪

1:42:39.666 --> 1:42:46.625
♪ Ever gets to define ♪

1:42:48.583 --> 1:42:51.666
♪ The life I'm meant to lead ♪

1:42:51.750 --> 1:42:57.333
♪ With this unruly heart ♪

1:42:57.416 --> 1:43:02.416
♪ Of mine ♪

1:43:04.583 --> 1:43:11.000
♪ Mine ♪

1:43:11.083 --> 1:43:14.041
♪ And nobody out there ♪

1:43:14.125 --> 1:43:18.125
♪ Ever gets to define ♪

1:43:18.208 --> 1:43:21.208
♪ The life I'm meant to lead ♪

1:43:21.291 --> 1:43:27.375
♪ With this unruly heart ♪

1:43:27.458 --> 1:43:34.416
♪ Of mine ♪

1:43:45.000 --> 1:43:47.708
This is too much.
It's too much for my heart.

1:43:47.791 --> 1:43:51.208
That's why I wanted you guys to see it.
I've never been more proud.

1:43:51.291 --> 1:43:53.791
-So when is the prom?
-There's no money left.

1:43:53.875 --> 1:43:56.750
-What? What do you mean?
-We already had a prom, remember?

1:43:56.833 --> 1:43:57.666
[Angie groans]

1:43:57.750 --> 1:44:00.375
[Principal Hawkins]
There could be a miracle. It's early.

1:44:00.458 --> 1:44:01.500
[Barry sighs]

1:44:02.625 --> 1:44:05.125
Okay, people,
it's Mickey and Judy time. Okay?

1:44:05.208 --> 1:44:07.375
This is the part
where we roll up our sleeves

1:44:07.458 --> 1:44:09.708
and we put on a prom
with our own bare hands.

1:44:09.791 --> 1:44:13.791
-We are giving Emma the prom she deserves.
-Okay, wait a minute.

1:44:13.875 --> 1:44:17.041
How much are we talking about?
What does a prom cost?

1:44:17.125 --> 1:44:18.000
[sputters]

1:44:18.083 --> 1:44:20.000
I mean,
it's not a school-sanctioned event,

1:44:20.083 --> 1:44:21.958
so we have to pay
a rental fee on the gym.

1:44:22.041 --> 1:44:22.916
DJ.

1:44:23.000 --> 1:44:24.541
-Lighting.
-Sound system.

1:44:24.625 --> 1:44:27.083
[Principal Hawkins]
It's still thousands of dollars.

1:44:27.750 --> 1:44:29.166
Right. Um…

1:44:32.166 --> 1:44:34.125
Okay, here.

1:44:35.250 --> 1:44:38.000
Charge that until it declines,
which will be soon.

1:44:38.083 --> 1:44:41.500
I had to declare bankruptcy
after my self-produced Notes on a Scandal.

1:44:42.208 --> 1:44:43.750
[Angie] Yes. Well…

1:44:45.083 --> 1:44:47.750
I don't have a credit card anymore
because I…

1:44:47.833 --> 1:44:49.166
Well, I just… [exhales]

1:44:49.250 --> 1:44:54.333
But, anyway, you can have what I have
in my Venmo and there's my cash.

1:44:54.416 --> 1:44:55.458
It's all yours.

1:44:55.541 --> 1:44:57.583
-Thanks, Angie. [chuckles]
-Sure.

1:44:57.666 --> 1:45:00.958
Okay. This is my card
from the Actors Federal Credit Union.

1:45:01.041 --> 1:45:03.458
Just cross your fingers and swipe.

1:45:04.375 --> 1:45:08.416
All right. Well, we're making
some progress here. This is a nice start.

1:45:08.500 --> 1:45:09.458
Um…

1:45:09.541 --> 1:45:12.000
-We still have a long way to go.
-[Angie] Mmm-hmm.

1:45:15.125 --> 1:45:16.291
[Angie clears throat]

1:45:16.375 --> 1:45:19.416
-Dee Dee. Dee Dee?
-What?

1:45:19.500 --> 1:45:23.291
Oh, come on. I know you've got
an American Express black card in there.

1:45:23.375 --> 1:45:24.875
There's no limit on that baby.

1:45:24.958 --> 1:45:30.000
Please, please, no.
I already gave a house.

1:45:30.083 --> 1:45:32.833
Exactly, so this is nothing. Come on.

1:45:34.791 --> 1:45:36.166
[seductively] Eleanor.

1:45:37.875 --> 1:45:39.083
Franklin.

1:45:40.500 --> 1:45:41.333
[sighs]

1:45:42.666 --> 1:45:49.625
[dramatically] Why does being good
cost so much… money?

1:45:49.708 --> 1:45:51.000
[all chuckling]

1:45:51.083 --> 1:45:53.000
-Well done, Dee Dee.
-[chuckles]

1:45:53.083 --> 1:45:54.916
-[Trent] Yes!
-We're fully financed.

1:45:55.000 --> 1:45:57.875
-[Trent] Yeah!
-Okay, well, let's give this girl a prom!

1:45:57.958 --> 1:45:59.875
-Yes!
-[Barry] Okay, let's do it!

1:45:59.958 --> 1:46:03.083
[Trent] The students will want to see us
perform some sort of number.

1:46:03.166 --> 1:46:06.541
So, look, I…
I've been thinking hard about this.

1:46:06.625 --> 1:46:07.458
[Barry] Mmm.

1:46:07.541 --> 1:46:10.250
That thing
that you and I were talking about.

1:46:11.166 --> 1:46:13.750
-I called your mother.
-What?

1:46:13.833 --> 1:46:16.875
Yeah, I found her number in your phone.

1:46:17.875 --> 1:46:19.750
How did you know my passcode?

1:46:19.833 --> 1:46:23.500
Well, I guessed. 9481. Beyoncé's birthday.

1:46:23.583 --> 1:46:26.041
[chuckling] Got it on the first try.

1:46:26.791 --> 1:46:30.041
-Well, why would you do that?
-Because, Barry…

1:46:31.875 --> 1:46:35.625
-I know you couldn't do it on your own.
-What did she say?

1:46:35.708 --> 1:46:38.625
Well, I think
maybe you should let her tell you that.

1:46:39.583 --> 1:46:40.583
[Vera] Hi, Barry.

1:46:42.291 --> 1:46:46.208
Okay. I'm gonna give you some space,
and I'll be in the faculty lounge, okay?

1:46:49.833 --> 1:46:53.583
No. No, you…
You don't get to do this. Okay?

1:46:53.666 --> 1:46:57.875
You don't get to show up
out of nowhere. Okay? No. Uh-uh.

1:46:57.958 --> 1:46:59.500
I came all this way, Barry.

1:46:59.583 --> 1:47:02.083
Well, you can just turn around
and go right back, okay?

1:47:02.166 --> 1:47:03.791
You called me, didn't you?

1:47:05.000 --> 1:47:07.666
That was you who called
and hung up, wasn't it?

1:47:11.125 --> 1:47:11.958
[sighs]

1:47:12.708 --> 1:47:17.541
I handled this all wrong, honey.
And I'm so sorry.

1:47:17.625 --> 1:47:19.666
Okay. You just… stay…

1:47:22.208 --> 1:47:26.500
When you told us what you were,
who you were,

1:47:27.916 --> 1:47:31.000
your father and I, we were scared.

1:47:31.083 --> 1:47:32.583
We hardly knew what gay meant.

1:47:32.666 --> 1:47:35.666
We both thought
that somehow we had failed you,

1:47:35.750 --> 1:47:37.458
like maybe it was our fault.

1:47:38.875 --> 1:47:41.166
-So it's okay now?
-[sighs]

1:47:41.250 --> 1:47:44.041
What I needed was a mother
who didn't know if it was okay

1:47:44.125 --> 1:47:45.666
but loved me anyway.

1:47:47.250 --> 1:47:49.958
You think you were scared?
How do you think I felt?

1:47:50.041 --> 1:47:53.083
[sobbing] I know, Barry.
I failed you and I know.

1:47:54.166 --> 1:47:57.083
That's gonna be on my heart
till the day I die.

1:47:57.750 --> 1:48:02.958
[voice breaking] But all I can say is
I was wrong and I'm sorry.

1:48:07.750 --> 1:48:09.666
What about Dad? Is he here?

1:48:09.750 --> 1:48:11.833
Uh, no. He's just not…

1:48:13.375 --> 1:48:14.541
He's not there yet.

1:48:15.125 --> 1:48:16.541
I'm sorry to say.

1:48:17.458 --> 1:48:18.458
Oh, Barry.

1:48:20.416 --> 1:48:25.250
Please forgive me.
I've missed you so much.

1:48:29.916 --> 1:48:31.250
[crying] I missed you too.

1:48:32.541 --> 1:48:33.583
I did.

1:48:34.791 --> 1:48:37.125
I missed you too. I missed you.

1:48:37.208 --> 1:48:39.125
[both sobbing]

1:48:42.416 --> 1:48:46.125
♪ Then you came along
And right or wrong… ♪

1:48:46.208 --> 1:48:50.166
-Aren't you tired of watching that?
-Eight million people have seen it.

1:48:50.791 --> 1:48:52.583
I just don't understand it.

1:48:52.666 --> 1:48:54.416
Well, I think it's brave.

1:48:55.208 --> 1:48:56.041
[sighs]

1:48:56.625 --> 1:48:58.833
The kids are saying
there's gonna be another prom.

1:48:58.916 --> 1:49:01.000
-[scoffs]
-Someone's offered to pay for it.

1:49:02.833 --> 1:49:03.750
Who?

1:49:04.958 --> 1:49:07.208
This is so generous of you guys.

1:49:07.291 --> 1:49:09.958
We had to do something
after you broke the Internet.

1:49:10.041 --> 1:49:13.000
It was crazy.
The numbers just kept going up,

1:49:13.083 --> 1:49:16.333
and then the Indiana Star called,
and then the Washington Post--

1:49:16.416 --> 1:49:17.833
Hello, everyone.

1:49:17.916 --> 1:49:20.041
Can't have a prom without flowers.

1:49:20.125 --> 1:49:22.083
So I will put these out on the table,

1:49:22.166 --> 1:49:24.166
even though I'd rather just
give them all to you.

1:49:24.250 --> 1:49:26.458
-[Angie] Oh, my God!
-[Barry] Is this for real?

1:49:26.541 --> 1:49:31.750
Can I just say you guys are
the best middle-aged people I've ever met.

1:49:32.500 --> 1:49:33.333
[exhales]

1:49:34.291 --> 1:49:35.166
That is…

1:49:35.250 --> 1:49:36.916
Oh, honey…

1:49:38.041 --> 1:49:41.250
We need to talk to you
about something, okay? And I think it's…

1:49:42.416 --> 1:49:44.541
It's important that you understand

1:49:44.625 --> 1:49:47.916
the real reason
why we came here to visit you.

1:49:48.000 --> 1:49:50.250
-It wasn't for the Hoosier pie?
-[chuckles]

1:49:50.333 --> 1:49:52.208
Well, I mean, um…

1:49:55.000 --> 1:49:57.541
-We were in a show.
-A wonderful show.

1:49:57.625 --> 1:49:58.875
Well, I mean…

1:49:59.750 --> 1:50:02.541
[hesitating]
And we got blasted by the critics.

1:50:02.625 --> 1:50:05.916
They called us narcissists, and it hurt.

1:50:06.000 --> 1:50:08.916
And it hurt
because I guess they were right.

1:50:09.000 --> 1:50:14.250
So we looked around for a cause
that might give us some credibility.

1:50:14.333 --> 1:50:16.625
[chuckling] Maybe get us some good press.

1:50:16.708 --> 1:50:19.458
Like building
a house for Habitat for Humanity.

1:50:19.541 --> 1:50:22.208
Then we realized that
we're not capable of building anything.

1:50:22.291 --> 1:50:23.958
And then I found you on Twitter.

1:50:24.041 --> 1:50:27.666
I mean, it was just dumb luck,
but meant to be.

1:50:28.791 --> 1:50:32.583
Well, I'm sorry to tell you this, but…

1:50:33.333 --> 1:50:35.541
you're going to build something.

1:50:35.625 --> 1:50:38.375
-You're going to build a prom.
-[all chuckling]

1:50:38.458 --> 1:50:40.416
Stop it! Stop this, please!

1:50:40.500 --> 1:50:43.041
Who gave you people
permission to be in here?

1:50:43.125 --> 1:50:46.208
-I did.
-You should have consulted with the PTA.

1:50:46.291 --> 1:50:49.958
Well, this is not a school event, so
I'm not obliged to get the PTA's approval.

1:50:50.541 --> 1:50:54.375
I'm going to be
as clear as I possibly can.

1:50:55.416 --> 1:50:58.208
Your beliefs are not our beliefs.

1:50:58.291 --> 1:51:00.166
Hey, Emma. Can we talk to you?

1:51:06.125 --> 1:51:09.083
I was a jerk, and I'm sorry.

1:51:09.875 --> 1:51:13.416
You deserve to go to prom
just like any other kid.

1:51:13.500 --> 1:51:17.500
What? I thought you hated me.
I thought you all hated me.

1:51:17.583 --> 1:51:18.916
Oh, they hated you.

1:51:19.000 --> 1:51:23.208
They hated you with a burning passion
stoked by centuries of intolerance

1:51:23.291 --> 1:51:25.291
and the lack of a drama program.

1:51:25.375 --> 1:51:26.791
I'm sorry, too, Emma.

1:51:28.500 --> 1:51:32.583
You know, you explain things really well.
You should be, like, a teacher.

1:51:32.666 --> 1:51:35.666
-Oh, you should be our drama teacher!
-[girl] Yes, please!

1:51:35.750 --> 1:51:37.416
You should do it. Do it.

1:51:38.916 --> 1:51:40.666
-You're hired!
-I'm a teacher!

1:51:40.750 --> 1:51:42.583
-As a temp.
-Absolutely.

1:51:42.666 --> 1:51:45.125
No, no, no! This is--
This is what I was afraid of.

1:51:45.208 --> 1:51:46.875
-Mom!
-Let me finish!

1:51:46.958 --> 1:51:50.416
No, you have got to stop talking
and just listen, okay?

1:51:52.500 --> 1:51:54.166
People don't turn gay.

1:51:55.250 --> 1:51:56.291
They are who they are.

1:51:56.375 --> 1:51:58.541
No. You don't know what you're saying.

1:51:58.625 --> 1:51:59.625
I do.

1:52:00.416 --> 1:52:01.333
I do.

1:52:03.541 --> 1:52:07.583
Look, I know how you were raised,
but… the world's a different place.

1:52:08.291 --> 1:52:10.083
And sure, it's not great, but…

1:52:11.083 --> 1:52:16.250
it's… it's better because of people
who have the courage to be who they are.

1:52:19.125 --> 1:52:20.291
People like her.

1:52:23.041 --> 1:52:24.333
[sighs]

1:52:24.916 --> 1:52:26.666
I don't want to hurt you.

1:52:28.041 --> 1:52:30.458
I don't want to hurt anyone.

1:52:33.083 --> 1:52:35.500
I just want to be me.

1:52:36.333 --> 1:52:37.250
[crying]

1:52:38.791 --> 1:52:40.041
So here goes.

1:52:40.750 --> 1:52:42.916
-I love you, Emma Nolan.
-Oh, my God.

1:52:43.500 --> 1:52:45.125
[all squeal and chuckle]

1:52:45.208 --> 1:52:47.041
I love you too.

1:52:47.125 --> 1:52:49.125
Alyssa… No, listen to me.

1:52:49.208 --> 1:52:52.750
You are very young and you are confused.

1:52:52.833 --> 1:52:54.541
You don't know what is…

1:52:59.875 --> 1:53:03.625
[voice breaking]
I just don't want you to have a hard life.

1:53:04.791 --> 1:53:06.416
It's already hard.

1:53:12.791 --> 1:53:14.416
-Mom, I love you--
-No. [shushes]

1:53:20.958 --> 1:53:22.458
We'll… [breathing shakily]

1:53:23.041 --> 1:53:27.750
We can talk about this tonight.
Okay? Okay?

1:53:27.833 --> 1:53:29.500
-Okay.
-Okay. Okay.

1:53:29.583 --> 1:53:30.750
Mom…

1:53:33.083 --> 1:53:34.000
[door opens]

1:53:34.083 --> 1:53:36.041
[crying]

1:53:36.625 --> 1:53:37.458
[door shuts]

1:53:38.500 --> 1:53:41.083
-[Emma whispers] Just breathe.
-Hey, why don't we decorate?

1:53:41.166 --> 1:53:43.875
Yes, let's decorate.
Let's decorate everything.

1:53:43.958 --> 1:53:45.833
-[Trent] All right.
-[Sheldon] I need you here.

1:53:45.916 --> 1:53:48.000
[Dee Dee] We're gonna
make this place really pretty.

1:53:58.750 --> 1:53:59.583
[Emma gasps]

1:54:03.583 --> 1:54:04.750
Look at that!

1:54:06.583 --> 1:54:09.583
I'm so proud of you. Look at what you did.

1:54:09.666 --> 1:54:11.333
I can't believe this.

1:54:12.583 --> 1:54:14.833
-[Emma gasps]
-[Alyssa] I think we're early.

1:54:14.916 --> 1:54:16.708
-Yeah, it looks like it.
-Mm-hmm.

1:54:16.791 --> 1:54:18.750
You want to hit up the punch bowl?

1:54:18.833 --> 1:54:22.583
No. There's only one thing
that I want to do.

1:54:23.958 --> 1:54:28.708
♪ I just wanna dance with you ♪

1:54:28.791 --> 1:54:35.083
♪ Let the whole world melt away
And dance with you ♪

1:54:35.166 --> 1:54:38.250
♪ Who cares
What other people say? ♪

1:54:38.333 --> 1:54:41.833
♪ And when we're through ♪

1:54:41.916 --> 1:54:48.291
♪ No one can convince us we were wrong ♪

1:54:48.375 --> 1:54:55.208
♪ All it takes is you and me ♪

1:54:56.291 --> 1:55:01.250
